</br>I'm the only person who never asks him...

00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:23.350
任何关于案子的问题 因为我不在乎
</br>any questions about his cases, because I don't care.

00:12:23.520 --> 00:12:25.290
而且他从不会因为我差劲而嫌弃我
</br>And he never judges me for being a terrible person.

00:12:25.320 --> 00:12:26.350
你确实很差劲
</br>Indeed you are.

00:12:26.440 --> 00:12:29.070
女士 布克 一起喝一杯吧
</br>Madame, Bouc, please join me for a drink, yes?

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:30.630
我只能陪你一小时
</br>You only have me for an hour.

00:12:30.800 --> 00:12:32.670
七点我就要上东方快车
</br>I ride on the Orient Express at seven,

00:12:32.760 --> 00:12:34.430
我担任总监
</br>official director business.

00:12:34.600 --> 00:12:36.150
我叔叔付了一大笔钱
</br>Uncle pays me absurdly

00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:37.680
让我在他豪华的火车上工作…
</br>to stay onboard his gorgeous train...

00:12:37.800 --> 00:12:38.910
并且离他的总部…
</br>and far away from him...

00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:40.190
很远…
</br>at the home office...

00:12:40.400 --> 00:12:41.830
置身于美酒佳肴之中
</br>consigned to wine and dine

00:12:41.920 --> 00:12:43.320
与美人权贵宴饮
</br>handsome officials for all eternity.

00:12:43.360 --> 00:12:44.580
裙带关系也是门艺术
</br>There is an art to nepotism.

00:12:44.760 --> 00:12:46.710
而你是其中的大师
</br>And you are its Michelangelo!

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:47.800
波洛先生
</br>Mr. Poirot.

00:12:47.880 --> 00:12:49.040
你也是个妓女吗
</br>Are you a prostitute as well?

00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:50.470
当然不是
</br>Certainly not.

00:12:50.560 --> 00:12:51.620
这个人烦到你了吗
</br>Is this man bothering you?

00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:52.990
快了
</br>He is about to.

00:12:53.160 --> 00:12:54.590
你是英国领事馆的人
</br>You are from the British consulate.

00:12:54.680 --> 00:12:56.350
是的 先生 是卡斯纳的案子
</br>I am, sir. It is the Kassner case.

00:12:56.960 --> 00:12:58.270
您怎么知道的
</br>Why, yes.

00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:00.230
我猜的没错吧
</br>I was correct in certain predictions?

00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:02.310
完全正确
</br>Quite.

00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:04.040
我不需要读这个电报
</br>I do not need to read the telegram.

00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:05.110
噢 有意思
</br>Oh, how fun.

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:06.750
有人出轨 还是死亡了
</br>Did someone cheat, or die?

00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:08.430
很不幸 两者都是
</br>Unfortunately, both.

00:13:11.080 --> 00:13:12.390
有人…
</br>Someone has...

00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:15.190
打断了我休息的计划
</br>interrupted my longing for rest.

00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:17.660
看来我今晚必须和你一起走了 布克
</br>It appears that I must travel with you tonight, Bouc.

00:13:17.840 --> 00:13:19.750
你能帮我在东方快车上找个车厢吗
</br>Can you find me a cabin on the Orient Express?

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:20.980
我的朋友…
</br>My friend...

00:13:21.160 --> 00:13:22.990
别的不好说 但我绝对
</br>I may not be good for much, but I sure as hell

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:24.390
能在我的火车上给你找张床…
</br>can get you a bed on my train...

00:13:24.560 --> 00:13:25.990
大冬天里三天的行程…
</br>in the dead of winter. Three days...

00:13:26.200 --> 00:13:30.030
无忧无虑 摆脱一切案子 你会爱上它的
</br>free of care, concern or crime. You will love it.

00:13:30.240 --> 00:13:32.830
女士 很高兴认识你
</br>Mademoiselle, it has been a pleasure. Sir.

00:13:33.520 --> 00:13:35.310
您的行李已经取走了
</br>Your luggage has been collected

00:13:35.400 --> 00:13:36.950
车费也付了
</br>and your expenses paid.

00:13:37.120 --> 00:13:38.870
您在加来下车…
</br>You will be met at Calais...

00:13:39.040 --> 00:13:41.420
有人会送您到多佛
</br>and then escorted to Dover,

00:13:41.520 --> 00:13:43.670
然后再坐火车到伦敦维多利亚站
</br>and then by rail to London Victoria.

00:13:43.880 --> 00:13:45.230
我想向您郑重表示感谢
</br>I would like to formally express gratitude.

00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:46.730
请别说了
</br>Please, don't speak.

00:13:46.760 --> 00:13:48.430
说得我心烦
</br>You make it worse.

00:13:55.680 --> 00:13:57.640
- 这是你的小费 伙计  - 谢谢 马奎兹先生
</br>- Here's a tip for you, pal.  - Thank you, Mr. Marquez.

00:13:57.760 --> 00:13:58.970
我都没帮您搬行李
</br>I didn't even carry your luggage.

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.140
噢 我这周过得不错
</br>Oh, I had a good week.

00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:01.910
走运的时候就得庆祝
</br>We celebrate when fortune smiles,

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.790
我们要分享好运
</br>and we share the good fortune.

00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:06.030
记得要说我们美国人的好话哈
</br>Remember to say nice things about us Americans, huh?

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:12.830
滚
</br>No!

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:14.030
嘿 站住
</br>Hey, stop!

00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:20.180
晚上好 先生
</br>Monsieur, bonsoir.

00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:21.550
雷切特先生
</br>For you, Mr. Ratchett,

00:14:21.640 --> 00:14:23.470
为您准备了我们这最好的位置
</br>the best table in the house.

00:14:28.600 --> 00:14:30.270
在这边 先生 最好的位置
</br>Just here, sir. The very best table.

00:14:30.440 --> 00:14:32.190
不 我要坐在这
</br>No, I want that one.

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:40.430
嘿 马思特曼 都安排好了吗
</br>Hey, Masterman. You got everything?

00:14:40.600 --> 00:14:42.670
那还用问吗 麦奎因先生
</br>Kind of you to inquire, Mr. MacQueen.

00:14:42.760 --> 00:14:44.590
我从不犯错
</br>I do not make mistakes.

00:14:47.280 --> 00:14:49.660
哦天啊 是安德烈伯爵
</br>Oh, my goodness! It's Count Andrenyi.

00:14:49.840 --> 00:14:50.900
快过来
</br>Come, come, come.

00:14:51.080 --> 00:14:53.830
我看过你在蒙特克里斯托跳舞
</br>I saw you dance at the Monte Cristo.

00:14:53.920 --> 00:14:55.710
我能给你拍张照吗
</br>Could I take your photograph?

00:15:05.120 --> 00:15:06.710
求你了 别打脸
</br>Please, my face, no!

00:15:29.960 --> 00:15:31.310
抱歉
</br>Sorry.

00:15:41.680 --> 00:15:44.270
东方快车…
</br>The Simplon Orient Express...

00:15:44.440 --> 00:15:48.060
经停索非亚 尼什 贝尔格莱德 温科夫齐 布罗德…
</br>with stops in Sofia, Niš, Belgrade, Vinkovci, Brod...

00:15:48.240 --> 00:15:50.430
可中转至布加勒斯特 萨格勒布
</br>with transfers to Bucharest, Zagreb,

00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:52.190
的里雅斯特 威尼斯 米兰 洛桑…
</br>Trieste, Venezia, Milan, Lausanne...

00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:54.510
第戎 巴黎 布伦 加来…
</br>Dijon, Paris, Boulogne, Calais...

00:15:54.720 --> 00:15:56.120
可前往多佛及伦敦
</br>with connection to Dover and London,

00:15:56.200 --> 00:15:57.340
十五分钟后出发
</br>leaves in fifteen minutes!

00:15:57.560 --> 00:15:59.630
这边 米歇尔 来贵客了
</br>This way, Michel! Precious cargo.

00:15:59.720 --> 00:16:01.350
我需要一张头等车票
</br>I need a first-class compartment.

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:03.430
好好照顾我的朋友 米歇尔
</br>Give special care to my friend, Michel.

00:16:03.560 --> 00:16:05.030
像国宝大熊猫一样的待遇
</br>I want him pampered like a zoo panda.

00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:06.250
可是布克先生 席位已经满了
</br>But Monsieur Bouc, we are fully booked.

00:16:06.280 --> 00:16:07.310
没有位置了
</br>There's no space left.

00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:09.360
想办法腾出来 可以安排十一号包厢
</br>Then we make space. He can have the number eleven.

00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:11.280
那里一般都安排给公务人员
</br>The eleven is always kept open for official use.

00:16:11.400 --> 00:16:12.710
非常舒适
</br>It's very comfortable.

00:16:12.880 --> 00:16:13.880
十一号有人了
</br>Eleven is taken.

00:16:13.920 --> 00:16:15.290
两天前一名奥地利教授预定的
</br>The Austrian professor booked it two days ago.

00:16:15.320 --> 00:16:16.440
整趟列车就找不到一个
</br>There is not one first-class

00:16:16.560 --> 00:16:17.760
头等包厢吗
</br>sleeper car on the whole train?

00:16:17.800 --> 00:16:18.800
找不到 先生
</br>Negative, sir.

00:16:18.960 --> 00:16:21.070
- 二等座呢  - 没位置了
</br>- Second-class?  - There's no space left at all.

00:16:21.240 --> 00:16:22.870
德贝纳姆小姐
</br>Mademoiselle Debenham.

00:16:23.080 --> 00:16:24.950
波洛先生 您也坐这趟列车吗
</br>Mr. Poirot, are you joining us?

00:16:25.120 --> 00:16:27.110
那得看他们俩谁说得赢谁
</br>It depends who wins this debate.

00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:28.590
所有的乘客都到了吗
</br>Have all the passengers arrived?

00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:31.310
还差一位 哈里斯先生
</br>All but one. Mr. Harris.

00:16:31.480 --> 00:16:32.840
“所有乘客必须至少
</br>"All passengers must check in

00:16:32.920 --> 00:16:35.000
提前半个小时检票…
</br>At least one half hour prior to time of departure...

00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:36.750
否则座位可能被收回”
</br>Or their seat may be forfeit."

00:16:36.920 --> 00:16:39.380
已经不到半小时了 收回座位
</br>The half hour has passed. The seat is forfeit.

00:16:39.600 --> 00:16:41.310
请把波洛先生的行李
</br>Please take Monsieur Poirot's luggage

00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:43.670
送到三号包厢 和麦奎因先生一间
</br>to number three with Mr. MacQueen.

00:16:43.840 --> 00:16:45.910
谢谢 布克 旅途愉快 我的朋友
</br>Merci, Bouc. Enjoy, my friend.

00:16:46.080 --> 00:16:47.470
欢迎您先生 谢谢
</br>Welcome, sir. Merci.

00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:52.910
数字“三”可不吉利
</br>Number three is unlucky.

00:16:56.480 --> 00:16:58.830
抱歉女生 刚才无意冒犯
</br>Apologies, madame. I meant no disrespect.

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:01.790
冒犯一下也没关系
</br>Well, you could try to mean a little.

00:17:02.680 --> 00:17:04.710
坐火车出行有一点
</br>One thing about train travel,

00:17:04.800 --> 00:17:06.750
难免会碰到一些人
</br>you're always knocking into somebody.

00:17:06.960 --> 00:17:08.070
很有趣
</br>It's wonderful.

00:17:08.240 --> 00:17:10.590
不过我还是想回去
</br>Though, I am looking forward to getting back.

00:17:10.800 --> 00:17:13.710
我爱旅行 爱辛辣的美食 异域风情 浪漫邂逅
</br>Travel is fine for spicy food, mosques, meeting men.

00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:17.190
但最终还是想念自己的床
</br>But eventually, you just miss your own bed.

00:17:20.120 --> 00:17:25.140
肯定有人会说我总是满世界地找老公
</br>I've been accused of husband hunting abroad.

00:17:26.360 --> 00:17:28.110
不过我还真不否认这点
</br>Well, I can't, in all honesty, deny it.

00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:30.390
虽然我喜欢独处 我是说真的
</br>I like my time alone, I do.

00:17:30.560 --> 00:17:32.630
不过 一个女人如果有钱的话
</br>But a lady has certain needs

00:17:32.720 --> 00:17:35.430
她的需求就该被满足…
</br>that deserve to be met if she has any money...

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:37.430
最好还是定期满足
</br>and preferably, on a regular basis.

00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:44.430
天呐 厨房着火了
</br>Oh, my! Fire in the kitchen!

00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:46.390
再会了 女士
</br>Farewell, madame.

00:17:47.360 --> 00:17:48.410
晚上好
</br>Good evening.

00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:49.440
晚上好
</br>Bonsoir.

00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:51.670
九号
</br>Number nine.

00:17:51.880 --> 00:17:53.630
晚上好
</br>Good evening. Bonsoir, bonsoir.

00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:55.310
你好吗 晚上好
</br>How you doing? Bonsoir.

00:17:55.560 --> 00:17:56.990
哦不好意思
</br>Oh. Excusez-moi.

00:17:57.160 --> 00:17:58.790
您先
</br>No, after you.

00:17:58.960 --> 00:18:00.150
谢谢
</br>Merci, merci.

00:18:02.280 --> 00:18:03.470
三号到了
</br>Ah number three.

00:18:04.720 --> 00:18:06.590
你是麦奎因先生吗
</br>You are Mr MacQueen?

00:18:06.760 --> 00:18:08.590
我想你走错包厢了
</br>Yeah. I think you might have the wrong berth.

00:18:10.320 --> 00:18:12.470
抱歉 有什么问题吗先生
</br>Sorry, is there a problem sir?

00:18:12.840 --> 00:18:14.110
没问题
</br>No, no problem.

00:18:14.520 --> 00:18:15.650
列车满了
</br>The train is full.

00:18:15.680 --> 00:18:20.470
我想我们 怎么说…算是室友了
</br>I think that we are, how do you say... "Bunkies."

00:18:22.160 --> 00:18:23.220
是吗
</br>Really?

00:18:23.400 --> 00:18:26.190
我也觉得很失望 这还不错
</br>I am equally disappointed in you. This is nice.

00:18:35.080 --> 00:18:36.760
跟上 宝贝儿
</br>Come along, darlings.

00:19:03.520 --> 00:19:04.660
不行
</br>No.

00:19:08.520 --> 00:19:09.660
不行
</br>No.

00:19:11.280 --> 00:19:12.340
这间呢
</br>This?

00:19:15.920 --> 00:19:18.300
怎么行李还没送来
</br>Why am I not yet unpacked?

00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:21.870
五分钟后发车
</br>Five minutes to departure.

00:19:21.960 --> 00:19:23.990
最后一次通知乘客
</br>Final call for passengers!

00:19:32.960 --> 00:19:34.750
我们要不要给你梳毛啊
</br>Shall we brush you?

00:19:34.920 --> 00:19:37.670
他们怎么磨蹭这么久
</br>What the hell is taking them so long?

00:19:37.840 --> 00:19:39.650
发车后让他们赶紧铺床
</br>Soon as we get out of here, have them make up the bed.

00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:40.970
都安排好了 雷切特先生
</br>It's already arranged, Mr. Ratchett.

00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:43.300
不 先把床铺好 再把我的录音机拿来
</br>No, I want the bed made. And bring my Dictaphone.

00:19:44.920 --> 00:19:46.190
连狗狗都上桌了
</br>Dogs on the table.

00:19:46.280 --> 00:19:48.470
真是我见过最恶心的事
</br>Most disgusting thing I've ever seen in my life.

00:19:48.640 --> 00:19:50.230
是的 先生 你去找麦奎因…
</br>Yes, sir. I want you to get MacQueen...

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:52.960
让他把米兰那笔买卖的单据全都拿来
</br>and have him bring every receipt from the Milan sale.

00:19:53.120 --> 00:19:54.520
现在就去 好的先生
</br>I want you to get it done. Yes, sir.

00:19:54.560 --> 00:19:56.110
现在就去
</br>I want you to get it done now.

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:03.380
不是让你马上就去吗 这就去 先生
</br>Did I say get it done now? Right away, sir.

00:21:04.640 --> 00:21:06.870
“你最好小心点”
</br>"Better watch yourself."

00:21:08.240 --> 00:21:09.830
您的咖啡 雷切特先生
</br>Your coffee, Mr. Ratchett.

00:21:13.400 --> 00:21:14.590
这是谁干的
</br>Who did this?

00:21:14.760 --> 00:21:16.590
我不知道 先生
</br>I can't say, sir.

00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:30.000
晚上好 哈伯德夫人
</br>Good evening, Mrs. Hubbard.

00:21:30.120 --> 00:21:31.720
你好 马斯特曼
</br>Hello there, Mr. Masterman.

00:21:48.760 --> 00:21:49.980
你好
</br>Well, hello.

00:21:52.120 --> 00:21:54.830
你再这么看下去 我就要收费了
</br>Eyes linger any longer, I'll have to charge rent.

00:21:55.480 --> 00:21:57.070
我很乐意付钱
</br>I'll pay.

00:21:57.440 --> 00:22:00.000
再来一杯吧
</br>Mmm. Have another drink.

00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.350
让您受辱了吗
</br>Are you insulted?

00:22:03.440 --> 00:22:05.630
只是有点失望罢了
</br>Hmm. Disappointed.

00:22:06.400 --> 00:22:09.150
有些人长得好看
</br>Some men have a good look.

00:22:09.320 --> 00:22:11.110
他们需要做的…
</br>All they have to do is...

00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:12.630
仅仅是把嘴闭上
</br>keep their mouth shut,

00:22:12.720 --> 00:22:14.590
就可以有所作为
</br>and they can take home any prize they want.

00:22:16.840 --> 00:22:19.950
可惜不 偏偏要开口说话
</br>Still, the mouth opens.

00:22:36.040 --> 00:22:37.550
没事吧 哈伯德夫人
</br>Is everything all right, Mrs. Hubbard?

00:22:37.720 --> 00:22:40.750
我觉得您的直觉非常敏锐
</br>You have a strong intuition, I know.

00:22:42.920 --> 00:22:45.830
我第二任丈夫也这么说
</br>My second husband used to say just so.

00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:48.990
等等 应该是第一任
</br>Hold that, it was my first.

00:22:49.160 --> 00:22:50.160
没错
</br>Yeah.

00:22:50.240 --> 00:22:52.030
他是我见过的最聪明的人
</br>Brightest man I ever met.

00:22:52.200 --> 00:22:55.310
长得像萝卜一样 不过我曾爱过那颗萝卜
</br>Face like a turnip, but I loved that turnip.

00:22:56.840 --> 00:22:58.830
和您聊天很愉快
</br>It was nice to talk.

00:23:05.360 --> 00:23:06.990
晚安
</br>Good night.

00:23:23.680 --> 00:23:25.280
波洛先生
</br>Monsieur Poirot?

00:23:25.400 --> 00:23:27.190
请进 米歇尔
</br>Entrez, Pierre Michel.

00:23:29.600 --> 00:23:30.600
您醒了
</br>Voilà.

00:23:30.720 --> 00:23:32.630
晚餐时…
</br>When you take supper...

00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:33.930
我会把麦奎因先生的东西
</br>I will move Monsieur MacQueen

00:23:33.960 --> 00:23:35.130
搬到布克先生的包厢
</br>into Monsieur Bouc's compartment.

00:23:35.160 --> 00:23:36.750
您享受头等舱待遇
</br>You travel first class, monsieur.

00:23:38.240 --> 00:23:40.750
太棒了 谢谢
</br>Ah, impeccable. Merci.

00:23:41.680 --> 00:23:42.680
用餐愉快
</br>Bon appétit.

00:23:42.840 --> 00:23:43.840
…这个鸡蛋
</br>...and the eggs?

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:07.870
下午好
</br>Good afternoon.

00:24:08.040 --> 00:24:09.310
哈伯德夫人
</br>Ah, Mrs. Hubbard.

00:24:09.480 --> 00:24:10.830
下午好
</br>Good afternoon.

00:24:12.400 --> 00:24:13.670
请慢用
</br>There we are.

00:24:13.840 --> 00:24:15.670
敬我们乘坐的东方快车
</br>Compliments of the Orient Express.

00:24:15.760 --> 00:24:17.270
谢谢 布克先生
</br>Thank you, Mr. Bouc.

00:24:17.440 --> 00:24:20.590
有什么需要 随时告诉我
</br>I am here for all of your needs.

00:24:20.760 --> 00:24:22.110
不 谢谢 我不喝酒
</br>No, thank you. I do not drink.

00:24:22.280 --> 00:24:24.580
您不喜欢喝酒吗
</br>It does not agree with you?

00:24:24.760 --> 00:24:27.550
我只是想远离罪恶
</br>Sin does not agree with me.

00:24:27.720 --> 00:24:30.950
恶习永远都是魔鬼的伙伴
</br>Vice is where the devil finds his darlings.

00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:33.110
那我就不打扰您了
</br>We should no longer speak.

00:24:34.880 --> 00:24:36.630
下午好
</br>Good afternoon.

00:24:36.800 --> 00:24:41.350
先生 要不要来杯开胃酒
</br>Monsieur. How about a apéritif?

00:24:41.520 --> 00:24:43.230
可惜我已经和火车上的负责人
</br>I regret I have an appointment

00:24:43.360 --> 00:24:45.350
约好了见面
</br>with the director of the train.

00:24:45.520 --> 00:24:47.900
他很快就要走了
</br>He was gonna leave anyway.

00:24:48.080 --> 00:24:51.070
没事 先生 女士您好
</br>Please, sir. Madame, madame.

00:24:51.240 --> 00:24:53.620
女士 女士
</br>Madame, madame.

00:24:54.240 --> 00:24:55.910
都安顿好了吗
</br>All settled in?

00:24:57.160 --> 00:24:59.870
都安排好了 都如广告所说那样
</br>Ah, merci! As advertised.

00:25:00.040 --> 00:25:03.870
不过 车上最好的可不是食物
</br>And yet, the best things on the train are not food.

00:25:07.240 --> 00:25:08.530
而是一群陌生人…
</br>You know there's something about...

00:25:08.560 --> 00:25:10.230
缘分使然坐上了同一趟列车
</br>a tangle of strangers pressed together

00:25:10.360 --> 00:25:11.850
一待就是几天…
</br>for days on end, with nothing in common...

00:25:11.880 --> 00:25:13.870
除此之外 毫无联系…
</br>but the need to go from one place to another...

00:25:14.040 --> 00:25:16.070
下车后就再也不见
</br>then never to see each other again.

00:25:16.280 --> 00:25:18.430
闲来无聊碰上萍水相逢…
</br>Boredom plus anonymity plus a...

00:25:18.600 --> 00:25:20.590
再配上这曼妙的晃动
</br>constant, gentle rocking.

00:25:21.600 --> 00:25:24.270
就你这样很难成大事
</br>With your hobbies, you will never amount to anything.

00:25:24.440 --> 00:25:25.910
我倒希望是这样
</br>God, I hope so. Hmm.

00:25:27.080 --> 00:25:28.430
我要点道鱼
</br>Order me the fish.

00:25:31.080 --> 00:25:33.430
把石斑鱼换成比目鱼
</br>Um, exchange grouper for sole,

00:25:33.560 --> 00:25:36.070
再把莴苣换成土豆…
</br>escarole for the potato, and...

00:25:37.080 --> 00:25:38.430
还有 牛肉汤换成骨汤
</br>the beef sauce for the velouté.

00:25:39.640 --> 00:25:43.390
服务员 这听上去很棒 给我也来一份
</br>Garéon, that sounds superb. The same for me.

00:25:45.800 --> 00:25:47.470
德拉戈米罗夫公主
</br>The Princess Dragomiroff.

00:25:48.200 --> 00:25:49.950
如果我为了钱和人结婚
</br>You know, if I ever were to marry for money,

00:25:50.040 --> 00:25:51.550
就找她这么有钱的
</br>I'd marry for that much money.

00:25:52.720 --> 00:25:53.940
早上我给达莉娅梳了毛
</br>I brushed Dalia this morning.

00:25:54.120 --> 00:25:56.750
不 我让你给我的小狗梳毛
</br>No, you tortured my darling doggy.

00:25:56.920 --> 00:25:58.140
你却在折磨她
</br>I asked you to brush her.

00:25:58.320 --> 00:26:00.470
你还是爱看狄更斯的书吗
</br>Are you still enjoying your Dickens?

00:26:00.640 --> 00:26:02.470
当然了 我的朋友
</br>Very much, mon ami.

00:26:02.640 --> 00:26:04.550
你这样光顾着看书和破案
</br>You know, with your books and your capers,

00:26:04.640 --> 00:26:06.310
很容易就错过艳遇
</br>you are missing out on romance.

00:26:07.480 --> 00:26:09.940
艳遇都是要付出代价的
</br>Romance never goes unpunished.

00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:11.990
我以前…
</br>There was, uh...

00:26:15.080 --> 00:26:17.790
也爱过一个人
</br>There was someone once.

00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:33.150
我希望之后别再让我坐在那个人旁边了
</br>I would prefer, in the future, to be sat not with that man.

00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:35.740
物以类聚 人以群分
</br>Like should be seated with like.

00:26:35.840 --> 00:26:37.790
我们并不是一类人
</br>We are not alike.

00:26:38.920 --> 00:26:40.270
不是所有人都会
</br>Not all of us are so concerned

00:26:40.360 --> 00:26:42.790
那么在意种族差异 教授
</br>with the separateness of races, Professor.

00:26:42.960 --> 00:26:45.190
我的坚持完全是
</br>It is out of respect for all kinds

00:26:45.320 --> 00:26:47.780
出于对所有种族的尊重
</br>that I prefer to keep them separate.

00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:50.950
如果把红酒和白酒混在一起
</br>To mix your red wine and the white

00:26:51.040 --> 00:26:52.990
两者就都毁了
</br>would be to ruin them both.

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:02.190
我喜欢桃红酒
</br>I like a good rosé.

00:27:45.760 --> 00:27:47.750
你好吗 不介意…
</br>Hey, how you doing? Would you mind...

00:27:47.920 --> 00:27:49.350
我坐在这里吧
</br>if I joined you?

00:27:50.600 --> 00:27:52.790
甜品是一种享受…
</br>Dessert is an indulgence...

00:27:52.960 --> 00:27:56.910
一个人独享就实在太蠢了
</br>and I feel kinda silly and stupid indulging alone.

00:27:57.080 --> 00:27:59.540
我一个人待着挺好的
</br>I am at my happiest alone.

00:28:00.280 --> 00:28:01.470
不过…
</br>But...

00:28:01.640 --> 00:28:04.430
看在你这份丹麦卷的份上
</br>for a small piece of your fragelité,

00:28:04.520 --> 00:28:05.580
一起吧
</br>please join me.

00:28:05.760 --> 00:28:09.190
好的 不好意思 再拿把叉子
</br>Oh, with pleasure. Excuse me, another fork?

00:28:11.880 --> 00:28:13.930
我一直想找机会认识你 波洛先生
</br>I've been trying to make your acquaintance, Mr. Poirot.

00:28:13.960 --> 00:28:14.960
谢谢
</br>Merci.

00:28:15.600 --> 00:28:19.380
我从来没有这么近距离的接触过名人
</br>I never ever sat so close to fame before.

00:28:19.560 --> 00:28:21.590
不对我说谎了
</br>No, I tell a lie.

00:28:21.800 --> 00:28:24.630
我曾和泰·柯布坐过一辆车
</br>Once, I was on a bus with Ty Cobb.

00:28:26.120 --> 00:28:28.420
底特律的球员
</br>Ball player, Detroit. Ah.

00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:33.950
你不介意我把顶上这些吃掉吧
</br>Would you mind if I have the little curly bit at the top?

00:28:34.120 --> 00:28:36.390
你还挺奇葩的
</br>You're an odd bird there.

00:28:37.440 --> 00:28:39.630
真是一个怪人
</br>You're a strange, peculiar man.

00:28:39.800 --> 00:28:40.860
到了这把年纪
</br>I am of an age

00:28:40.960 --> 00:28:42.910
我很清楚自己想要什么 不要什么
</br>where I know what I like and what I do not like.

00:28:43.080 --> 00:28:45.950
喜欢的东西尽情享受
</br>What I like, I enjoy enormously.

00:28:46.120 --> 00:28:48.470
不喜欢的绝不容忍
</br>What I dislike, I cannot abide.

00:28:48.640 --> 00:28:51.150
比如 谈生意前 人们都爱说的
</br>For instance, the temporary pleasantries

00:28:51.280 --> 00:28:53.990
那些客套话 我就很讨厌
</br>before what is determined to be a business discussion.

00:28:54.640 --> 00:28:56.110
你很有趣
</br>You're fun.

00:28:57.440 --> 00:28:58.470
好吧
</br>All right.

00:28:59.600 --> 00:29:01.830
我想雇你做一件事
</br>I would like to offer you a job.

00:29:03.640 --> 00:29:05.670
报纸称呼您为
</br>"The avenger of the innocent."

00:29:05.760 --> 00:29:07.130
“为清白而战的复仇者”
</br>It's what they call you in the papers.

00:29:07.160 --> 00:29:08.470
你是清白之人吗
</br>And you are an innocent?

00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:10.270
我是个商人
</br>I'm a businessman.

00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:15.270
我是个艺术商人 我是说 我还是个新手
</br>I'm an art dealer. I mean, I'm new to it.

00:29:15.480 --> 00:29:18.270
但是刚开始运气就挺好的
</br>But my beginner's luck has panned out.

00:29:19.160 --> 00:29:20.750
文物 古董
</br>Relics, antiquities.

00:29:20.920 --> 00:29:24.110
地毯 奇怪的玩意 东方的物品
</br>Rugs, weird. Orientals.

00:29:25.080 --> 00:29:29.510
我是刚入行的 所以眼光有些业余
</br>I'm new to the game, so I got the amateur eyeball.

00:29:29.680 --> 00:29:33.510
不过我觉得那些 呃…
</br>But I got a little problem with these, uh...

00:29:33.680 --> 00:29:35.750
所谓的鉴定师有点儿问题
</br>so-called appraisers.

00:29:35.960 --> 00:29:37.870
其中任何一个都不能相信
</br>You can't trust a one of 'em.

00:29:40.160 --> 00:29:41.990
我的一些顾客…
</br>Some of my customers...

00:29:43.040 --> 00:29:44.180
他们买了点东西…
</br>they buy a piece...

00:29:44.360 --> 00:29:48.470
然后发现那些东西是赝品…
</br>they find out that they're not exactly original...

00:29:48.680 --> 00:29:50.030
不能说是我的错…
</br>which is hardly my fault...

00:29:50.200 --> 00:29:53.870
谁知道卡香丝绸围巾是假货
</br>if a Kashan silk scarf is a fake.

00:29:54.040 --> 00:29:55.100
对吧
</br>Right? Huh?

00:29:55.280 --> 00:29:56.500
没错
</br>C'est bon.

00:29:58.880 --> 00:30:01.390
但事情是我结下了点儿梁子
</br>But I've managed to make a few enemies, is the thing.

00:30:01.560 --> 00:30:04.710
我收到一些信 有人在威胁我
</br>I got a few letters, people making threats.

00:30:05.720 --> 00:30:08.350
我认为 很可能是那些意大利人
</br>I think, most likely, it's the Italians.

00:30:08.960 --> 00:30:12.950
我在米兰卖给他们一套东方地毯
</br>I sold them a set of Oriental carpets in Milan.

00:30:14.240 --> 00:30:18.070
然而买家对其来源不是很满意
</br>And the buyers weren't so happy with the provenance.

00:30:19.320 --> 00:30:22.230
他们想要把本钱和利润都要回去 你懂吧
</br>And they want their money back with interest, you know?

00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:23.320
意大利人
</br>Italians.

00:30:24.040 --> 00:30:25.390
他们就是这样
</br>A guinea's a guinea.

00:30:26.400 --> 00:30:29.990
接着迎面而来一位大侦探
</br>And then comes along the genius detective.

00:30:30.160 --> 00:30:31.380
我吗
</br>Me?

00:30:31.600 --> 00:30:34.990
- 是的 就是你 赫拉克勒斯 波罗  - 赫尔克里
</br>- Yes, you. Hercules Poirot.  - Hercule.

00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:38.310
呃…
</br>Um...

00:30:38.520 --> 00:30:39.830
我要说我想要做的事情
</br>Here's what I'd like to do.

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:43.030
我想要雇你保护我…
</br>I would like to hire you to watch my back...

00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:45.270
直到我安全到达某地
</br>until I get someplace safe.

00:30:46.520 --> 00:30:48.750
这对你来说是很容易到手的钱
</br>It's easy money for you.

00:30:48.920 --> 00:30:50.750
我也是为了心安 你知道吧
</br>And it's peace of mind for me, you know?

00:30:50.920 --> 00:30:52.590
我明白了 很好
</br>I understand. Good.

00:30:52.760 --> 00:30:53.760
我拒绝
</br>I refuse.

00:30:53.840 --> 00:30:55.870
抱歉 那就不好了
</br>I'm sorry? That's bad.

00:30:57.120 --> 00:31:00.350
或许我说的不够清楚
</br>Maybe I didn't make myself clear enough.

00:31:00.520 --> 00:31:04.510
你看 有人要对我不利
</br>You see, someone's out to get me.

00:31:04.680 --> 00:31:08.550
我知道我并不是什么好人 也绝不可能是
</br>And I know I'm not the best guy born, not by a long shot.

00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:10.350
如果死后有另一个世界
</br>And if there's a world after this one,

00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:12.710
我会和你一样面临审判
</br>I will face judgment just like you.

00:31:12.800 --> 00:31:13.800
但是…
</br>But...

00:31:16.400 --> 00:31:19.750
我还不急着去那儿
</br>I ain't in no goddamn rush to do it.

00:31:20.200 --> 00:31:22.110
你在拿枪指着我吗 不是
</br>You're holding a gun on me? No.

00:31:22.280 --> 00:31:24.910
不是你 是这个世界
</br>Not you. On the world.

00:31:25.080 --> 00:31:27.460
我存在于世界 不要用枪指着我
</br>I exist in the world. Do not point a gun at me.

00:31:27.640 --> 00:31:29.310
一个星期一万如何
</br>How's ten thousand sound for a week?

00:31:29.480 --> 00:31:31.520
确实慷慨 雷切特先生 我必须拒绝
</br>It's a generous offer, Mr. Ratchett. I must decline.

00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:32.640
一万五呢
</br>Fifteen thousand?

00:31:32.720 --> 00:31:33.920
你没听见我的说的 我拒绝
</br>You didn't hear me. I decline.

00:31:34.040 --> 00:31:35.470
噢 我懂了
</br>Oh, I get it.

00:31:36.400 --> 00:31:41.150
对于伟大的赫拉克勒斯 波罗来说 这事儿不够光彩 是吧
</br>It's not flashy enough for the great Hercules Poirot, huh?

00:31:41.320 --> 00:31:42.380
没有闪光灯…
</br>No flashbulbs...

00:31:42.560 --> 00:31:43.610
你卖假货给匪徒
</br>You sell fakes to gangsters.

00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:45.270
你得承担后果
</br>You're suffering the consequences.

00:31:45.440 --> 00:31:47.550
我找出罪犯 但我不保护他们
</br>I detect criminals. I do not protect them.

00:31:49.120 --> 00:31:51.230
所以你是拒绝我的脏钱
</br>So you say "No" To my dirty money.

00:31:51.400 --> 00:31:53.310
我是拒绝你 雷切特先生
</br>I say "No" To you, Mr. Ratchett.

00:31:54.320 --> 00:31:56.590
是枪的事儿 对吧 就是这个吗
</br>Business with the gun, right? Is that what it was?

00:31:56.760 --> 00:31:58.950
更多的是个人原因
</br>It is far more personal than that.

00:32:00.680 --> 00:32:02.670
我不喜欢你的脸
</br>I do not like your face.

00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:06.990
请允许我先行离开
</br>If you will excuse me.

00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:10.150
你喜欢我的蛋糕 对吧
</br>You liked my cake, didn't you?

00:32:10.360 --> 00:32:11.750
蛋糕棒极了
</br>The cake was excellent.

00:32:11.840 --> 00:32:14.270
祝您有个愉快的下午 雷切特先生
</br>Have a pleasant afternoon, Mr. Ratchett.

00:32:38.840 --> 00:32:40.030
谢谢你
</br>Thank you.

00:32:40.880 --> 00:32:43.260
噢 真是冷
</br>Ooh! Cold.

00:32:58.240 --> 00:32:59.350
唔
</br>Hmm.

00:33:04.080 --> 00:33:06.270
心爱的凯瑟琳
</br>Mysweet Katherine.

00:33:08.520 --> 00:33:09.790
我的爱
</br>My love.

00:33:19.400 --> 00:33:22.230
狄更斯先生
</br>Mr. Dickens.

00:33:36.760 --> 00:33:38.110
雷切特先生
</br>Mr. Ratchett?

00:33:46.280 --> 00:33:48.030
雷切特先生
</br>Mr. Ratchett?

00:33:48.280 --> 00:33:49.390
没事
</br>It's nothing.

00:33:51.400 --> 00:33:52.070
好的 先生
</br>Very good sir.

00:33:52.120 --> 00:33:53.120
晚安
</br>Good night.

00:34:14.280 --> 00:34:15.280
哈伯德夫人吗
</br>Mrs. Hubbard?

00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:17.230
是哈伯德夫人
</br>It's always Mrs. Hubbard.

00:34:17.400 --> 00:34:18.870
哈伯德夫人
</br>Mrs. Hubbard.

00:35:13.520 --> 00:35:15.350
我们都死了吗
</br>Did we die?

00:35:15.520 --> 00:35:18.190
女士们先生们 列车脱轨了
</br>Ladies and gentlemen, the train has been derailed.

00:35:18.880 --> 00:35:20.490
你一切都好吗 马奎兹先生
</br>Are you all right, Mr. Marquez?

00:35:20.520 --> 00:35:22.430
我很好 谢谢
</br>I'm fine. Thank you.

00:35:22.520 --> 00:35:23.650
待在车厢里是最安全的
</br>You'll be safest in your cabins.

00:35:23.680 --> 00:35:24.990
布克先生明早…
</br>Mr. Bouc will speak to you all...

00:35:25.160 --> 00:35:26.190
会和大家说明
</br>in the morning.

00:35:26.320 --> 00:35:27.650
请待在车厢里 那是最安全的
</br>Please, you will be safest in your cabins.

00:35:27.680 --> 00:35:28.870
当然
</br>Of course.

00:35:29.040 --> 00:35:30.870
我们要死了吗
</br>Are we gonna die?

00:35:36.240 --> 00:35:37.380
噢…
</br>Oh...

00:35:39.560 --> 00:35:41.350
我的凯瑟琳
</br>MyKatherine.

00:35:43.560 --> 00:35:45.510
我美丽的…
</br>Mybeautiful...

00:36:28.640 --> 00:36:30.710
女士们先生们 我很抱歉
</br>Ladies and gentlemen, I am afraid

00:36:30.800 --> 00:36:33.310
我们的列车依然无法行动
</br>that our train is still unable to go anywhere.

00:36:33.480 --> 00:36:34.540
是的 快要掉下去了
</br>Yeah, except down.

00:36:34.720 --> 00:36:36.360
我们还要在这儿待多久呢
</br>How long are we supposed to just sit here?

00:36:36.480 --> 00:36:38.860
是啊 得有人做点儿什么
</br>Yes, someone must be doing something.

00:36:39.040 --> 00:36:41.910
我确实做了点事儿 我什么也不用做
</br>Of course I am doing something. I am doing nothing.

00:36:42.080 --> 00:36:44.510
准确来说两个小时十分钟之前
</br>Precisely two hours and ten minutes ago,

00:36:44.600 --> 00:36:46.630
当我们没有按时到达布罗德…
</br>when we did not arrive in Brod as scheduled...

00:36:46.800 --> 00:36:48.920
站长必定会猜到我们的处境…
</br>the station master will have surmised our situation...

00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:51.710
他已经派遣一队人来挖掘引擎…
</br>and already dispatched a team to excavate the engine...

00:36:51.880 --> 00:36:54.110
为我们清理道路 然后让我们能再次踏上旅程
</br>clear our path, and send us on our way.

00:36:54.280 --> 00:36:55.470
在那之前 我保证…
</br>Until then, I assure you...

00:36:55.640 --> 00:36:59.030
我们会为你们提供充足的食物和温暖舒适的服务
</br>we will all be made warm and fed and comfortable.

00:36:59.720 --> 00:37:00.880
我们可以步行
</br>We could walk.

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:03.670
我们会在冷风中被冻死
</br>We could die of exposure trying.

00:37:03.840 --> 00:37:05.750
我还要换乘呢
</br>I have a connection to make.

00:37:05.920 --> 00:37:08.790
我的船后天就从法国出发了
</br>My boat sails day after tomorrow from France.

00:37:09.280 --> 00:37:12.550
我打赌你上不了船 我也到不了伦敦
</br>Without you, I'd wager. Or me in London.

00:37:12.720 --> 00:37:16.230
我希望你能对我损失的时间负责 布克先生
</br>I hold you accountable for my loss of time, Mr. Bouc.

00:37:16.400 --> 00:37:18.170
女士 你不能让我对这种天气负责
</br>Madam, you cannot hold me accountable for the weather.

00:37:18.200 --> 00:37:20.270
我当然可以 谁让你是负责人
</br>Of course I can. You're the one here.

00:37:20.440 --> 00:37:22.550
我在都灵的会议怎么办
</br>And my conference in Turin?

00:37:22.760 --> 00:37:24.950
我还要去索肖的汽车工厂和人会面呢
</br>And I was to meet at the auto factory in Sochaux.

00:37:25.480 --> 00:37:27.860
是的 有些事情 是掌握在上帝手上的
</br>Yes, some things, they are in God's hands.

00:37:28.440 --> 00:37:30.430
我们是否能安全抵达目的地…
</br>It is not for us to say...

00:37:30.640 --> 00:37:34.030
不是我们说了算的…
</br>if we deserve to arrive safely at our destination...

00:37:35.200 --> 00:37:39.030
<font size="40" color="#ece0c2">撒旦：路西法，传说中的堕落天使
{\rCHS}或者像<u>撒旦</u>我们注定堕落
</br>or if, like <u>Lucifer</u>, we must fall.</font>

00:37:50.080 --> 00:37:52.460
您的早餐 雷切特先生
</br>Breakfast for you, Mr. Ratchett.

00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:55.950
啊 你好 马斯特曼先生
</br>Ah, Bonjour, Mr. Masterman.

00:37:57.480 --> 00:37:58.870
有什么问题吗
</br>There is a problem?

00:37:59.040 --> 00:38:00.470
我没法确定 先生
</br>I can't say, sir.

00:38:00.640 --> 00:38:02.070
雷切特先生
</br>Mr. Ratchett?

00:38:11.120 --> 00:38:13.390
抱歉
</br>Excuse me.

00:38:16.280 --> 00:38:17.790
有冷风
</br>That is cold air.

00:38:17.960 --> 00:38:19.910
请立刻让布克先生过来
</br>Please bring Monsieur Bouc immediately,

00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:21.950
还有阿巴斯诺特医生
</br>and also Dr. Arbuthnot.

00:38:42.600 --> 00:38:44.310
老天爷啊
</br>Good God!

00:38:44.480 --> 00:38:46.830
除了尸体 什么也不要碰
</br>Touch nothing else, only the body.

00:38:50.320 --> 00:38:52.390
我的天 太可怕了
</br>My God, this is horrible.

00:38:52.600 --> 00:38:55.060
先是暴风雪 现在又是…
</br>First the snow, now...

00:38:55.240 --> 00:38:56.410
我得去站台通知警方
</br>I'll have to meet with the police

00:38:56.440 --> 00:38:58.240
并说明情况
</br>and make some statement in some grimy station.

00:38:58.320 --> 00:39:00.430
有个人死在这儿了
</br>And a man has died.

00:39:01.320 --> 00:39:02.750
有人死在这里
</br>And a man has died.

00:39:02.920 --> 00:39:05.030
他是被捅死的
</br>He was stabbed.

00:39:05.200 --> 00:39:06.340
是一把长刀
</br>Long, straight-edged knife.

00:39:06.520 --> 00:39:08.110
身上有多处伤口 有些很浅
</br>Multiple stab wounds, some shallow,

00:39:08.240 --> 00:39:09.710
有些直插入肌肉
</br>some cut clean through muscle.

00:39:09.880 --> 00:39:11.450
左撇子还是右撇子
</br>Left-hand side or right-hand side?

00:39:11.480 --> 00:39:13.190
这是个问题
</br>That's the thing.

00:39:13.360 --> 00:39:15.110
这个凶手可能
</br>It appears the killer

00:39:15.200 --> 00:39:17.550
闭上了眼睛然后摸黑捅的
</br>maybe closed his eyes and struck blind.

00:39:17.720 --> 00:39:21.150
你能估算出死亡时间吗
</br>Can you estimate the time of death?

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:23.670
窗户开着很难推算出时间…
</br>It's hard to say with the window open...

00:39:23.880 --> 00:39:26.750
但是很有可能是在午夜和凌晨两点之间
</br>but my best guess is between midnight and 2:00.

00:39:26.880 --> 00:39:28.250
但是那个时候没有人进入他的车厢
</br>But no one went in his compartment then.

00:39:28.280 --> 00:39:29.390
我整夜都在站岗
</br>I sat in my seat all night.

00:39:29.480 --> 00:39:32.470
如果有人进去我肯定会看见 这不可能
</br>I would have seen if someone went in. It's impossible.

00:39:34.200 --> 00:39:36.170
谢谢你 医生 请回餐车吧
</br>Thank you, Doctor. Please, return to the dining car.

00:39:36.200 --> 00:39:38.190
米歇尔 保护这个车厢
</br>Michel, secure this carriage.

00:39:40.440 --> 00:39:41.830
波罗
</br>Poirot.

00:39:45.120 --> 00:39:47.070
我需要你的帮助 我的朋友
</br>I need your help, my friend.

00:39:50.480 --> 00:39:51.910
你得找出是谁干的
</br>You have to find who did this.

00:39:52.080 --> 00:39:53.190
拜托了 我代表
</br>Please, I implore you,

00:39:53.280 --> 00:39:54.870
东方快车恳求你
</br>on behalf of the Orient Express.

00:39:55.000 --> 00:39:56.000
在警察到的时候
</br>When the police arrive,

00:39:56.120 --> 00:39:57.250
我们能够告诉他们事件已经解决了
</br>we can present them with the case closed.

00:39:57.280 --> 00:39:59.310
只有你能够救我了
</br>You are the only one who can save me.

00:39:59.480 --> 00:40:01.630
你的真诚打动了我 亲爱的
</br>Your faith touches me, mon cher.

00:40:01.720 --> 00:40:03.470
但是我必须好好享受假期
</br>But I must have this rest.

00:40:03.640 --> 00:40:06.670
那就把它当作在海滨的小游戏
</br>Well, think of it as a little beachside puzzle.

00:40:06.880 --> 00:40:08.750
对你来说不算什么
</br>That's nothing to your mind!

00:40:08.920 --> 00:40:10.990
你查看一下那些乘客的经历
</br>You look up the antecedents of the passengers.

00:40:11.160 --> 00:40:12.360
看他们有没有说实话
</br>You establish their bona fides.

00:40:12.400 --> 00:40:14.550
你就做你该做的 你…你…
</br>Then you do what you do. You... You... You...

00:40:14.760 --> 00:40:19.070
你就坐在椅子上吃着蛋糕…
</br>You sit in a chair and you eat your cake...

00:40:19.240 --> 00:40:21.390
然后思考着直到真相浮出水面
</br>and you think until the solution presents itself.

00:40:21.600 --> 00:40:23.530
不然坐在冰天雪地里还能干什么
</br>What else are you going to do while we sit here in the snow?

00:40:23.560 --> 00:40:24.680
头脑没有连续的刺激
</br>Without constant stimulation,

00:40:24.720 --> 00:40:26.250
你的脑细胞会饿死的
</br>your little gray cells will starve and die.

00:40:26.280 --> 00:40:27.690
你觉得那就是我要做的吗 坐在椅子上…
</br>You think that is what I do? I sit in a chair...

00:40:27.720 --> 00:40:28.770
吃着一小块蛋糕
</br>and I have a little piece of cake,

00:40:28.800 --> 00:40:30.090
然后我就能想到一个很好的办法了吗
</br>and then I come up with a great idea?

00:40:30.120 --> 00:40:31.610
我不知道你是如何处理的 我有我的狄更斯
</br>I don't know what you do. I have my Dickens.

00:40:31.640 --> 00:40:33.230
去你的狄更斯吧
</br>Damn your Dickens!

00:40:34.080 --> 00:40:35.280
如果我们把这个留给警察
</br>If we leave this to the police,

00:40:35.320 --> 00:40:36.480
他们会找出一个凶手…
</br>they will choose a culprit...

00:40:36.640 --> 00:40:38.710
不管对与错 他们会吊死他
</br>right or wrong, and they will hang him.

00:40:38.880 --> 00:40:40.070
很可能是马奎兹先生…
</br>Most probably Mr. Marquez...

00:40:40.240 --> 00:40:42.390
只因为他的名字叫做马奎兹
</br>for no other reason than his name is Marquez.

00:40:42.560 --> 00:40:45.190
或者是阿巴斯诺特医生 因为他的肤色
</br>Or Dr. Arbuthnot for the color of his skin.

00:40:50.680 --> 00:40:53.710
你是唯一可以带来正义的人
</br>You are the only one who can bring justice.

00:40:56.960 --> 00:40:58.010
给我一张列车的地图
</br>Let me have a map of this coach.

00:40:58.040 --> 00:40:59.040
没问题
</br>Of course.

00:40:59.120 --> 00:41:00.120
每一位乘客的通行证 所有的一切
</br>Every passport. Anything.

00:41:00.200 --> 00:41:02.070
安排和所有乘客进行面谈
</br>Interviews arranged with all of our passengers.

00:41:02.240 --> 00:41:05.270
搜集证据 理清顺序 找出方法 直到凶手出现
</br>Evidence, order and method, until one culprit emerges.

00:41:05.480 --> 00:41:07.270
我不能容忍谋杀 我的朋友
</br>I do not approve of murder, my friend.

00:41:07.480 --> 00:41:08.480
我们每天都会遇到
</br>Every day, we meet people

00:41:08.560 --> 00:41:09.650
一些没有他们世界会变得更好的人…
</br>the world could do better without...

00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:10.900
然而我们不能杀死他们
</br>yet we do not kill them.

00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:13.710
我们不能和野兽相提并论
</br>We must be better than the beasts.

00:41:15.520 --> 00:41:17.900
所以让我们找到这个凶手
</br>So let us find this killer.

00:41:18.120 --> 00:41:19.630
发生什么了
</br>What's going on?

00:41:22.200 --> 00:41:24.990
女士们先生们 允许我 呃…
</br>Ladies and gentlemen, allow me to, um...

00:41:25.160 --> 00:41:27.790
似乎我们的运气更加糟糕了
</br>It appears that our bad luck has worsened.

00:41:28.000 --> 00:41:29.000
有…
</br>That is...

00:41:29.160 --> 00:41:32.150
一名乘客死在了列车上
</br>A passenger has died on the train.

00:41:32.320 --> 00:41:33.950
雷切特先生
</br>Monsieur Ratchett.

00:41:43.200 --> 00:41:44.830
看起来他们最后还是出手了
</br>Looks like they got him after all.

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:46.950
你觉得他是被杀的吗
</br>You assume he was killed?

00:41:47.120 --> 00:41:48.670
不 不
</br>No, no.

00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:51.510
我只是说他身体十分健康
</br>I just mean he was in perfectly good health.

00:41:51.680 --> 00:41:53.150
然后他树敌很多 就这样
</br>He had his enemies, that's all.

00:41:53.360 --> 00:41:55.350
确实是这样 他被杀死了
</br>Indeed, he did. He was murdered.

00:41:56.960 --> 00:41:59.790
我的老天 谋杀 发生在这儿吗
</br>Good God. Murder, here?

00:41:59.960 --> 00:42:01.180
很不幸 女士
</br>Alas, madame.

00:42:01.360 --> 00:42:03.190
愿上帝保佑他的灵魂安息
</br>God rest his soul.

00:42:04.240 --> 00:42:06.030
有人半夜在我的车厢里
</br>Someone was rummaging around my cabin

00:42:06.120 --> 00:42:07.390
翻找东西
</br>in the middle of the night.

00:42:07.560 --> 00:42:09.550
没有人相信我
</br>Nobody would believe me.

00:42:11.640 --> 00:42:12.670
现在是什么情况
</br>What is going on?

00:42:12.880 --> 00:42:14.000
就在我们被雪困住之际
</br>As we are snowbound,

00:42:14.040 --> 00:42:15.360
我已经受我的朋友布克先生的委托…
</br>I have elected to take the case...

00:42:15.440 --> 00:42:17.950
接手这个案件并找出凶手
</br>and find for my friend, Monsieur Bouc, the criminal.

00:42:18.120 --> 00:42:19.750
为什么是你
</br>And why you?

00:42:20.880 --> 00:42:22.750
我是赫拉克勒斯 波罗…
</br>My name is Hercule Poirot...

00:42:22.920 --> 00:42:25.550
我可能是世界上最伟大的侦探
</br>and I am probably the greatest detective in the world.

00:42:26.080 --> 00:42:27.410
我会及时找你们谈话
</br>I will speak to all of you in time.

00:42:27.440 --> 00:42:28.750
现在…
</br>For the moment...

00:42:28.920 --> 00:42:30.130
我必须建议你们待在
</br>I must recommend that you remain

00:42:30.160 --> 00:42:31.690
车厢内并把门锁好
</br>in your compartments with the doors locked.

00:42:31.720 --> 00:42:33.390
我觉得跟个囚犯一样
</br>I feel like a prisoner here.

00:42:33.560 --> 00:42:35.940
这是为你们自身的安全着想
</br>It is for your own safety.

00:42:36.120 --> 00:42:38.230
如果发生了一起谋杀案…
</br>If there was a murder...

00:42:38.400 --> 00:42:40.390
那就有一个凶手
</br>then there was a murderer.

00:42:41.400 --> 00:42:43.270
而凶手在我们身边…
</br>The murderer is with us...

00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:47.110
就在列车上 就现在
</br>on the train, now.

00:42:57.760 --> 00:43:00.990
两个车厢之前的门在晚上是锁着的对吗
</br>The doors between coaches were locked at night, hmm?

00:43:01.160 --> 00:43:02.990
当然 我亲自锁的
</br>Absolutely. Done myself.

00:43:03.160 --> 00:43:04.290
列车已经被搜查了
</br>The train's been searched.

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:05.690
列车上下都没人躲着
</br>There's no one hiding on it or under it.

00:43:05.720 --> 00:43:08.020
这样我们就可以缩小我们搜索的范围
</br>We can therefore limit our investigation

00:43:08.120 --> 00:43:10.550
至加来车厢的乘客
</br>to the occupants of the Calais coach.

00:43:10.720 --> 00:43:12.630
布克 你来协助我
</br>Bouc, you will assist me.

00:43:12.800 --> 00:43:14.570
因为你是唯一在另一个车厢住的乘客…
</br>As the only traveler who slept in another coach...

00:43:14.600 --> 00:43:16.590
你是唯一没有嫌疑的人
</br>you are the only one who is not a suspect.

00:43:25.200 --> 00:43:28.670
麦奎因先生 现在是喝酒的时候吗
</br>Mr. MacQueen, is this really the time for drinking?

00:43:28.840 --> 00:43:30.590
我老板死了
</br>My boss is dead.

00:43:30.760 --> 00:43:32.390
我失业了
</br>I'm out of a job,

00:43:32.480 --> 00:43:34.110
然后你感觉是我干的一样
</br>and you're looking at me like I did it.

00:43:34.280 --> 00:43:35.500
我们还没有定论
</br>We make no accusations.

00:43:35.680 --> 00:43:36.950
你认识他
</br>You knew him, so from here

00:43:37.040 --> 00:43:38.360
所以现在我们有必要整理一下重要事实
</br>we must glean the essential facts.

00:43:38.520 --> 00:43:40.350
你是他的亲戚吗
</br>Were you his relative?

00:43:41.160 --> 00:43:43.990
不是 我是秘书
</br>No, his secretary.

00:43:45.480 --> 00:43:49.830
我给他订票 定餐
</br>Book his travel, order his steaks.

00:43:50.000 --> 00:43:51.220
我从没见过像这样
</br>The man ate more steak

00:43:51.320 --> 00:43:53.430
吃这么多牛排的人
</br>than I've ever seen in my entire life.

00:43:53.600 --> 00:43:55.750
他以前做古董生意
</br>He was in antiques.

00:43:55.920 --> 00:43:57.470
没有售卖资格证
</br>He had no qualification for it,

00:43:57.560 --> 00:43:58.680
没有做生意的眼色和说辞
</br>not the eye or the languages.

00:43:59.280 --> 00:44:02.670
事实上 他没有经商 或是会计头脑…
</br>Truth is, he had no head for business, accounting...

00:44:02.840 --> 00:44:04.150
没有
</br>none of it.

00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:05.510
我解决所有事情
</br>I took care of everything.

00:44:05.680 --> 00:44:08.140
他雇佣你多久了
</br>How long were you in his employ?

00:44:08.320 --> 00:44:11.150
还有二十天就满一年了
</br>Twenty days shy of a year.

00:44:11.320 --> 00:44:14.940
我不喜欢禁令…
</br>Prohibition wasn't to my taste...

00:44:16.920 --> 00:44:19.910
所以当我醒悟时 我一人在海外还负着债
</br>so I found myself overseas, and in debt.

00:44:23.200 --> 00:44:25.790
我学的法律…
</br>I'm a lawyer by education...

00:44:25.960 --> 00:44:27.790
但不是职业律师
</br>not disposition.

00:44:27.960 --> 00:44:30.110
我十分不擅长这行业
</br>I was downright awful at it.

00:44:30.880 --> 00:44:32.150
你喜欢他吗
</br>You were fond of him?

00:44:32.320 --> 00:44:34.700
我喜欢他的钱
</br>I was fond of his money.

00:44:34.880 --> 00:44:35.990
雷切特是个蛮人…
</br>Ratchett was crude...

00:44:36.560 --> 00:44:41.270
要求苛刻 辱骂他人 几乎像个囚徒
</br>demanding, insulting, and most likely a felon.

00:44:41.440 --> 00:44:43.270
你上次见他是什么时候
</br>When did you last see him?

