00:53:13.480 --> 00:53:15.590
- 去确认一件事  - 什么事
</br>- To confirm a suspicion.  - Which was?

00:53:15.760 --> 00:53:17.150
我不太喜欢说那个
</br>That I wouldn't like it.

00:53:17.320 --> 00:53:18.990
我在波士顿有了一份工作
</br>I was offered a post in Boston.

00:53:19.160 --> 00:53:20.830
我去了波士顿 然后直接回伦敦
</br>Saw Boston, went straight back to London.

00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:22.310
雷切特是波士顿人吗
</br>Is that where Ratchett was from?

00:53:22.400 --> 00:53:23.710
波士顿 我不太知道
</br>Boston? I can't says I know.

00:53:25.040 --> 00:53:26.230
这不太合适…
</br>It wouldn't be proper...

00:53:26.720 --> 00:53:28.030
去问
</br>to ask.

00:53:29.960 --> 00:53:30.960
继续
</br>Carry on.

00:53:31.120 --> 00:53:32.510
我最后看见…
</br>I last saw...

00:53:32.680 --> 00:53:35.910
雷切特先生是在九点钟
</br>Mr. Ratchett at nine o'clock.

00:53:36.080 --> 00:53:40.150
我给他端来咖啡 挂了他的衣服
</br>I brought his coffee and hung up his clothes.

00:53:44.680 --> 00:53:47.060
我觉得你有牙痛
</br>You have a toothache, I think.

00:53:48.000 --> 00:53:50.070
我预约了这周在伦敦拔牙
</br>I've got an extraction booked in London this week.

00:53:50.240 --> 00:53:53.750
雷切特先生坚决要求我这事别拖了
</br>Mr. Ratchett insisted on not putting it off any longer.

00:53:53.920 --> 00:53:55.120
他说他厌倦了
</br>He said he was tired of hearing

00:53:55.200 --> 00:53:56.260
听我强忍着呻吟
</br>my suppressed groans.

00:53:56.440 --> 00:53:57.560
这富有同情心的罗切特…
</br>This sympathetic Ratchett...

00:53:57.720 --> 00:54:00.280
他经常在晚上喝咖啡吗
</br>was it his usual practice to drink coffee at night?

00:54:00.440 --> 00:54:04.710
从不 但他最近很焦躁
</br>Not at all. But he'd been very agitated lately.

00:54:04.880 --> 00:54:08.790
说他想保持警觉些 尤其是在大晚上
</br>Said he wanted to stay alert, especially so last night.

00:54:08.960 --> 00:54:11.340
他在他房间发现了一封信
</br>He found a letter in his compartment.

00:54:12.560 --> 00:54:14.550
请告诉我这不是你干的
</br>Please tell me you didn't do this.

00:54:14.720 --> 00:54:16.210
如果我要把什么不好的东西
</br>If I were to leave something unpleasant

00:54:16.240 --> 00:54:17.350
放在你枕头上的话 先生…
</br>on your pillow, sir...

00:54:17.560 --> 00:54:19.150
那不会是一封信的
</br>it would not be a letter.

00:54:20.160 --> 00:54:21.590
拿咖啡来
</br>Coffee.

00:54:24.280 --> 00:54:25.470
当然了…
</br>Surely, such a...

00:54:25.880 --> 00:54:28.670
一个像你这么规矩又细心的仆人…
</br>proper and precise valet...

00:54:28.840 --> 00:54:30.750
不可能会这样和主人说话吧
</br>would never speak to his master as you did?

00:54:31.760 --> 00:54:36.270
除非他知道他的工作即将突然…
</br>Unless he knew his career was coming to a sudden...

00:54:37.360 --> 00:54:38.750
结束
</br>end.

00:54:40.360 --> 00:54:42.990
不仅是因为牙疼吧 我想
</br>No mere toothache, I think.

00:54:44.240 --> 00:54:45.300
是肺癌吗
</br>The lungs?

00:54:48.160 --> 00:54:49.710
是甲状腺癌
</br>The thyroid.

00:54:50.440 --> 00:54:51.500
已经蔓延到胃了
</br>Spread now to stomach.

00:54:51.640 --> 00:54:54.270
和我父亲一样的病 我比他还早了五年
</br>Same as got my father, five years younger.

00:54:56.040 --> 00:54:57.670
顶多还有几个月了
</br>Months at best.

00:54:59.400 --> 00:55:01.390
恐怕手术也无法治愈了 医生说
</br>"Inoperable, I'm afraid," said the doctor.

00:55:01.560 --> 00:55:04.550
然后突然地…我就不害怕了
</br>And suddenly, I wasn't... afraid.

00:55:05.400 --> 00:55:08.430
从此我只做我想做的事
</br>I would only do what I wanted from here on.

00:55:08.600 --> 00:55:09.660
我现在有话直说
</br>I speak my mind now.

00:55:11.200 --> 00:55:12.390
说说咖啡吧
</br>The coffee.

00:55:13.080 --> 00:55:15.030
看上去他的杯子里掺了巴比妥(镇静安眠用)
</br>It appears that his cup was laced with barbital.

00:55:15.120 --> 00:55:16.200
你肯定会告诉我
</br>You, of course, will tell me

00:55:16.240 --> 00:55:17.330
这不是你放的吧
</br>that you did not put it in there.

00:55:17.360 --> 00:55:18.360
当然不是我
</br>Of course I didn't.

00:55:18.800 --> 00:55:19.990
你是什么时候 从哪里
</br>When and from where

00:55:20.080 --> 00:55:21.950
取来的咖啡和杯子
</br>did you procure the coffee and the cups?

00:55:22.440 --> 00:55:23.750
从厨房里 先生
</br>In the kitchen, sir.

00:55:23.960 --> 00:55:28.150
我晚餐时点了咖啡 九点去取 我去时咖啡已准备好了
</br>I ordered it at dinner to be ready at 9:00, and so it was.

00:55:28.320 --> 00:55:31.510
任何人都可能在我之前对它动手脚
</br>Anybody could have got a hold of it before me.

00:55:32.000 --> 00:55:33.220
谢谢你的配合
</br>Merci.

00:55:39.200 --> 00:55:40.910
马斯特曼先生
</br>Mr. Masterman.

00:55:41.320 --> 00:55:43.350
对你的牙疼我感到很遗憾
</br>I'm sorry about the toothache.

00:55:52.080 --> 00:55:53.270
谢谢
</br>Merci.

00:55:53.440 --> 00:55:55.430
我喜欢小蛋糕
</br>I love the little cakes.

00:55:56.760 --> 00:55:59.190
那么 皮埃尔 埃斯特拉瓦多斯小姐 你是传教士…
</br>So, Miss Pilar Estravados, you are a missionary...

00:55:59.360 --> 00:56:00.400
但是在你改行之前
</br>but you trained as a nurse

00:56:00.440 --> 00:56:01.840
曾受过做护士的训练 是吗
</br>before you changed professions, yes?

00:56:02.640 --> 00:56:04.030
这是我欠上帝的
</br>I owed it to God.

00:56:04.200 --> 00:56:06.580
你有什么罪过吗
</br>You owed Him a debt?

00:56:07.920 --> 00:56:09.510
我曾经一度…
</br>There were...

00:56:11.240 --> 00:56:14.070
很放纵…
</br>indulgent times in my life...

00:56:15.000 --> 00:56:18.590
只知索取而不知给予
</br>when I took more than I gave.

00:56:18.760 --> 00:56:20.030
吉哈特 哈德曼
</br>Gerhard Hardman.

00:56:20.200 --> 00:56:22.870
工程学教授
</br>Professor of engineering.

00:56:23.040 --> 00:56:25.790
科学才能为德国
</br>It is science that will win back

00:56:25.880 --> 00:56:27.590
赢回他的尊严
</br>for Germany her pride.

00:56:27.760 --> 00:56:29.750
- 贝尼亚米诺 马奎兹  - 马奎兹先生
</br>- Biniamino Marquez.  - Mr. Marquez.

00:56:29.920 --> 00:56:31.060
听着 为希望你们弄清楚
</br>Listen, I wanna be clear

00:56:31.200 --> 00:56:32.600
我与这件案子 没有任何关系…
</br>of any association with the crime...

00:56:32.640 --> 00:56:33.750
所以请随意问我吧
</br>so please ask me anything.

00:56:33.920 --> 00:56:36.220
问什么都行 我不再撒谎了
</br>Anything. I never lie anymore.

00:56:36.400 --> 00:56:38.390
昨晚你离开过房间吗
</br>Did you leave your compartment at all last night?

00:56:38.560 --> 00:56:41.710
只离开过一次 我去拿阿司匹林
</br>Only once, to get an aspirin.

00:56:41.880 --> 00:56:44.440
赫伯德夫人之前给了我点药
</br>Mrs. Hubbard offered me something earlier.

00:56:44.600 --> 00:56:46.550
我开始拒绝了 但我睡不着时…
</br>I declined at first, but when I couldn't rest...

00:56:46.720 --> 00:56:48.390
我就去向她要了
</br>I went to ask for it.

00:56:48.560 --> 00:56:50.790
我在都灵有个会议
</br>My conference is in Turin.

00:56:50.960 --> 00:56:52.830
我是出席的唯一的奥地利人
</br>I am the only Austrian to present,

00:56:52.920 --> 00:56:54.670
也就是说 如果我不在…
</br>which means without me...

00:56:54.840 --> 00:56:56.910
会议就达不到标准了
</br>the talks will be substandard.

00:56:57.080 --> 00:56:58.350
然后我就越狱了
</br>Then I escaped prison,

00:56:58.440 --> 00:57:00.070
贿赂了些人 到了美国
</br>and I bribed myself into the US.

00:57:00.240 --> 00:57:02.670
发誓再也不撒谎盗窃了
</br>where I swore never to lie or steal again.

00:57:02.840 --> 00:57:04.210
因为你看 我的朋友
</br>You see, my friends, because when people

00:57:04.240 --> 00:57:05.630
人们信任你 就会从你这多买东西
</br>trust you, they buy more.

00:57:05.800 --> 00:57:09.420
意大利人就像奶牛 西班牙人像绵羊
</br>The Italians are cows. The Spaniards, sheep.

00:57:09.600 --> 00:57:11.430
比利时人像…
</br>The Belgians...

00:57:13.040 --> 00:57:14.710
我到自己房间
</br>I come to my room, which I share

00:57:14.800 --> 00:57:17.670
我和那英国来的闷闷不乐的男管家住
</br>with the unhappy English butler.

00:57:17.840 --> 00:57:20.190
那家伙 他老是呻吟
</br>A fish. He groans a lot.

00:57:20.360 --> 00:57:23.270
但我肯定他看着我睡了一夜到天亮
</br>But I'm sure he saw me sleep all night until morning.

00:57:23.960 --> 00:57:25.070
我应该要说…
</br>I should say...

00:57:25.240 --> 00:57:27.830
说不定与案子有关…
</br>in case it is relevant...

00:57:28.000 --> 00:57:30.350
有个场面很尴尬
</br>there was an embarrassing moment.

00:57:30.520 --> 00:57:32.550
我去看赫伯德夫人时…
</br>When I went to see Mrs. Hubbard...

00:57:32.760 --> 00:57:34.590
我开始开错了门
</br>first, I opened the wrong door.

00:57:35.440 --> 00:57:37.070
噢 抱歉
</br>Oh, sorry.

00:57:37.240 --> 00:57:38.380
这时是几点
</br>What time was this?

00:57:38.600 --> 00:57:39.960
那应该是大约…
</br>That must have been about...

00:57:40.080 --> 00:57:41.350
不要说抱歉
</br>Don't be sorry.

00:57:42.320 --> 00:57:44.310
…十点四十分
</br>...twenty minutes to 11:00.

00:57:45.160 --> 00:57:47.150
有意思
</br>This is interesting.

00:57:47.320 --> 00:57:48.460
就目前所知
</br>As far as it is known,

00:57:48.560 --> 00:57:51.350
你是最后一个看见雷切特活着的人
</br>you are the last person to see Ratchett alive.

00:57:53.560 --> 00:57:55.070
- 你做什么工作  - 推销汽车
</br>- Your business?  - Automobiles.

00:57:55.280 --> 00:57:56.630
我有三个展示厅
</br>I have three showrooms.

00:57:56.800 --> 00:57:59.910
来美国时我一无所有 现在…
</br>I come to America with nothing. And now...

00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:01.090
如果你说的属实
</br>If what you say is true,

00:58:01.120 --> 00:58:02.170
德贝纳姆小姐会证实的
</br>Miss Debenham will confirm it.

00:58:02.200 --> 00:58:04.110
但我说的是真的
</br>But it is true.

00:58:04.280 --> 00:58:08.150
我不会说谎的
</br>I would not lie.

00:58:08.320 --> 00:58:09.990
德贝纳姆小姐可能离开房间
</br>May it be possible that Miss Debenham

00:58:10.080 --> 00:58:11.760
而不被你注意到吗
</br>left your compartment without you noticing?

00:58:12.040 --> 00:58:14.630
不可能 我睡得很浅
</br>No. I sleep very lightly.

00:58:14.840 --> 00:58:17.830
听到一点点声音我都会醒来坐直
</br>The slightest sound and I bolt upright.

00:58:19.720 --> 00:58:21.710
我受过一次惊吓
</br>I was surprised once.

00:58:23.400 --> 00:58:25.270
不会有第二次了
</br>Never again.

00:58:25.480 --> 00:58:27.350
不 我没说我是司机
</br>No, I didn't say I was a chauffeur.

00:58:27.560 --> 00:58:29.940
从你行李里掉出来的照片中…
</br>The photographs that spilled out of your luggage...

00:58:30.120 --> 00:58:31.910
有一张很漂亮的
</br>there was a beautiful one

00:58:32.000 --> 00:58:34.110
上面是个戴着司机的帽子的小男孩…
</br>with a little boy wearing a chauffeur's hat...

00:58:34.320 --> 00:58:35.670
在看望工作中的爸爸
</br>visiting his papa at work.

00:58:35.840 --> 00:58:37.430
你是谁的司机
</br>Who did you chauffeur?

00:58:38.680 --> 00:58:40.110
埃斯特拉瓦多斯小姐 为什么你的手上
</br>Miss Estravados, why do your hands

00:58:40.200 --> 00:58:41.870
有拳击手该有的老茧呢
</br>have the calluses of a boxer?

00:58:42.080 --> 00:58:43.870
我在危险的城市工作…
</br>I do my work in dangerous cities...

00:58:44.760 --> 00:58:46.950
我不能被恐惧支配
</br>where I cannot be governed by fear.

00:58:47.520 --> 00:58:48.520
我练过拳击
</br>I trained to fight.

00:58:48.680 --> 00:58:50.270
但自从那次惊吓后…
</br>But you do not trust your god anymore...

00:58:50.440 --> 00:58:51.870
你就不在信任你的上帝了吗
</br>since your surprise?

00:58:52.040 --> 00:58:54.550
不 以免上帝太忙碌
</br>No, in case He is busy.

00:58:55.040 --> 00:58:56.790
上帝总是忙碌的
</br>God is always busy.

00:58:57.600 --> 00:58:58.910
是马斯特曼干的
</br>It's Masterman.

00:58:59.080 --> 00:59:00.720
一个濒死的人没什么可失去的
</br>A man dying is a man with nothing to lose.

00:59:00.840 --> 00:59:02.920
很好 布克 但是马奎兹先生…
</br>Bravo, Bouc. Except for the problem of Mr. Marquez...

00:59:03.000 --> 00:59:04.000
已经证实
</br>who has now confirmed

00:59:04.080 --> 00:59:05.280
与他同铺的马斯特曼…
</br>that his bunkmate, Masterman...

00:59:05.400 --> 00:59:08.230
在雷切特死亡的时候 正在床上睡觉
</br>was reading in his bed at the time of death.

00:59:08.440 --> 00:59:10.820
如果这么容易 我也不会出名了 下一个
</br>If it were easy, I would not be famous. Next.

00:59:19.440 --> 00:59:20.440
德贝纳姆小姐…
</br>Miss Debenham...

00:59:20.600 --> 00:59:22.230
你不介意我们在室外吹点风吧
</br>you do not mind to brace the air?

00:59:22.400 --> 00:59:23.950
我们为你准备了野餐
</br>For you, we have the picnic.

00:59:25.280 --> 00:59:27.710
却让我得室友在狭窄的车厢里受审
</br>While you made my roommate suffer cramped quarters.

00:59:27.800 --> 00:59:28.860
我明白了
</br>I see.

00:59:29.080 --> 00:59:30.110
选择最合适的地方
</br>Choose the best location

00:59:30.200 --> 00:59:31.720
来从不同的嫌疑人口中套出真话
</br>to extract the truth from each suspect.

00:59:31.920 --> 00:59:33.830
让她紧张 而让我受冻
</br>Put her off-balance and me, freeze.

00:59:34.240 --> 00:59:35.240
聪明
</br>Clever.

00:59:35.400 --> 00:59:36.650
可以请你写下你的全名
</br>Will you write down your full name

00:59:36.680 --> 00:59:38.350
和地址吗
</br>and address, please?

00:59:38.520 --> 00:59:40.190
顺便说一下 我的睡袍是淡紫色的
</br>A pale mauve, by the way.

00:59:40.360 --> 00:59:41.670
埃斯特拉瓦多斯小姐和我说 你问了
</br>Miss Estravados told me you asked

00:59:41.760 --> 00:59:43.350
她睡袍的颜色
</br>the color of her dressing gown.

00:59:46.200 --> 00:59:47.550
谢谢
</br>Merci.

00:59:47.720 --> 00:59:50.020
玛丽 赫迈奥妮 德贝纳姆
</br>"Mary Hermione Debenham."

00:59:50.560 --> 00:59:52.750
你被人叫做赫迈奥妮过吗
</br>Do you ever go by Hermione?

00:59:52.920 --> 00:59:55.870
我没被雇佣作德贝纳姆老师时 别人一直叫我玛丽
</br>A constant Mary, when I'm not employed as Miss Debenham.

00:59:55.960 --> 00:59:57.180
我是左撇子
</br>Left-handed.

00:59:57.920 --> 01:00:00.190
不大寻常 我知道
</br>Unusual, I know.

01:00:00.360 --> 01:00:01.530
你不能就这么妄下结论
</br>You mustn't have your theory fixed

01:00:01.560 --> 01:00:03.230
如果你在检查我的笔迹的话
</br>if you're testing my handwriting.

01:00:03.400 --> 01:00:05.390
你对死者怎么看
</br>What did you think of the dead man?

01:00:05.920 --> 01:00:08.830
呃 我只能说 我没怎么想过他
</br>Uh, I can't say I did think about him.

01:00:10.520 --> 01:00:11.930
我不太明白你问题的意义
</br>I don't quite see the point of your question.

01:00:11.960 --> 01:00:15.950
喔 原谅我小小的发挥 小姐
</br>Oh, forgive me, mademoiselle, my little originalities.

01:00:17.440 --> 01:00:19.870
人性错综复杂 总是反常的
</br>Human nature is perverse in its complexity.

01:00:20.040 --> 01:00:23.870
要挖掘人性 需要正确的工具
</br>To plumb it, it takes the right tools.

01:00:24.040 --> 01:00:25.750
这些是玩具 不是工具 赫尔克里
</br>These are toys, not tools, Hercule.

01:00:26.200 --> 01:00:27.340
我建议你把它们放一边吧
</br>I prefer you put them away.

01:00:27.560 --> 01:00:29.190
直接的办法呢 冻糕
</br>The direct method? Parfait.

01:00:29.360 --> 01:00:31.590
乘车之前你认识那医生吗
</br>You knew the doctor before traveling?

01:00:31.760 --> 01:00:32.760
阿巴斯诺特医生
</br>Dr. Arbuthnot?

01:00:34.560 --> 01:00:35.620
不认识
</br>No.

01:00:38.160 --> 01:00:40.110
却如此一见钟情吗
</br>But such instant attraction?

01:00:43.600 --> 01:00:44.910
我们不是在美国…
</br>We are not in America...

01:00:45.120 --> 01:00:46.470
德贝纳姆小姐 没有法律禁止
</br>Miss Debenham. There are no laws

01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:48.830
你这样的情感
</br>against what you may feel.

01:00:52.160 --> 01:00:55.310
也没有法律禁止我保持沉默 对此…
</br>Nor are there laws against silence, of which...

01:00:55.480 --> 01:00:57.070
我保持…
</br>I hold my...

01:00:59.520 --> 01:01:01.710
我从未去过美国
</br>I've never been to America.

01:01:03.680 --> 01:01:07.790
或许我可以问问一些…
</br>Perhaps I may ask about some...

01:01:07.960 --> 01:01:09.150
我碰巧听见的话吗
</br>words I overheard?

01:01:09.320 --> 01:01:11.150
你和这位陌生人 阿巴斯诺特
</br>You and the stranger, Arbuthnot,

01:01:11.240 --> 01:01:13.310
比陌生人的关系更亲近
</br>are closer than strangers might be.

01:01:13.520 --> 01:01:15.510
你说…
</br>You said...

01:01:15.680 --> 01:01:19.950
现在不行 等我们成了 没人能阻止我们
</br>"Not now. When we are done. Then no one can touch us."

01:01:20.120 --> 01:01:21.750
你是什么意思
</br>What did you mean?

01:01:23.200 --> 01:01:25.910
你觉得我是在说谋杀吗
</br>You think I meant murder?

01:01:26.080 --> 01:01:28.870
对一个拿着锤子的人来说 每个问题都是钉子
</br>To a man with a hammer, every problem is a nail.

01:01:29.080 --> 01:01:30.710
你活在犯罪中
</br>You live crime.

01:01:30.880 --> 01:01:33.030
- 你每天都目睹罪恶  - 并不是
</br>- You see evil every day.  - Not so.

01:01:33.200 --> 01:01:34.670
我见过足够多的犯罪
</br>I see enough crime to know

01:01:34.760 --> 01:01:37.670
我知道 犯罪行为是反常的
</br>that the criminal act is the anomaly.

01:01:37.880 --> 01:01:40.830
我相信 谋杀一个人…
</br>I believe it takes a fracture of the soul...

01:01:41.280 --> 01:01:43.710
会带走灵魂的一部分
</br>to murder another human being.

01:01:46.120 --> 01:01:49.070
我再问一遍 你的话是什么意思
</br>I ask again, what did you mean?

01:01:51.360 --> 01:01:53.270
我们已达成一致…
</br>As we established...

01:01:53.480 --> 01:01:56.310
没有法律禁止我保持沉默
</br>there are no laws against my silence.

01:01:58.160 --> 01:01:59.670
很好
</br>Very well.

01:02:09.560 --> 01:02:12.230
那么之后呢 德卓戈米罗夫公主
</br>And afterwards, Princess Dragomiroff?

01:02:12.400 --> 01:02:14.780
晚餐后 我上床睡觉
</br>After dinner, I came to bed.

01:02:15.840 --> 01:02:18.510
上帝赐我长寿
</br>God blessed me with long life,

01:02:18.600 --> 01:02:21.990
却给了我这带病的背 让我痛苦
</br>but cursed me with a bad back to make it miserable.

01:02:22.680 --> 01:02:25.240
大约十二点四十五分…
</br>About a quarter to 1:00...

01:02:25.400 --> 01:02:26.830
我叫来施密特小姐
</br>I called for Fraulein Schmidt.

01:02:26.920 --> 01:02:28.430
- 嗯哼  - 她替我按摩…
</br>- Mmm-hmm.  - She massaged me...

01:02:28.640 --> 01:02:29.860
给我读了一会书
</br>and read to me for a while.

01:02:29.960 --> 01:02:31.790
- 然后我就睡了  - 嗯哼
</br>- Then I sleep.  - Mmm-hmm.

01:02:32.320 --> 01:02:33.540
您和阿姆斯壮一家…
</br>Were you ever acquainted...

01:02:33.720 --> 01:02:37.110
熟悉吗
</br>with a family by the name of Armstrong?

01:02:44.520 --> 01:02:47.950
他们遭受过无法言说的不幸
</br>They endured an unspeakable tragedy.

01:02:48.160 --> 01:02:51.590
我很仰慕索尼娅 阿姆斯壮的母亲…
</br>I was an admirer of Sonia Armstrong's mother...

01:02:51.760 --> 01:02:53.910
女演员 琳达·亚登
</br>Linda Arden, the actress.

01:02:54.120 --> 01:02:57.110
百年难见的天才
</br>A once-a-century talent.

01:02:58.120 --> 01:03:01.270
亚登小姐本准备转做导演
</br>Miss Arden was to turn to directing.

01:03:01.920 --> 01:03:03.670
倘若没有那场悲剧
</br>She would have become the first

01:03:03.800 --> 01:03:06.100
<font size="40" color="#ece0c2">百老汇：纽约市重要的南北向道路
是美国戏剧和音乐剧的重要发扬地，因此成为了音乐剧的代名词
{\rCHS}她本能成为<u>百老汇…</u>
</br>woman titan of <u>Broadway...</font></u>

01:03:06.280 --> 01:03:08.190
第一位女巨人
</br>were it not for the tragedy.

01:03:08.360 --> 01:03:11.980
这位琳达·亚登 她去世了吗
</br>And this Linda Arden, she is dead?

01:03:12.160 --> 01:03:13.990
她要是去世了倒还好些
</br>She might as well be.

01:03:14.960 --> 01:03:16.550
她不再离开家
</br>She no longer leaves her home.

01:03:19.040 --> 01:03:21.670
黛西是我的教女
</br>Daisy was my goddaughter.

01:03:22.880 --> 01:03:24.710
她是个…
</br>She was a...

01:03:35.280 --> 01:03:38.430
我不明白这和我们的问题有什么关系 侦探先生
</br>I don't see how this relates to our troubles, Detective.

01:03:38.600 --> 01:03:42.190
昨晚被杀的男人 他的真名是卡塞蒂
</br>The man killed last night, his true name was Cassetti.

01:03:42.360 --> 01:03:45.430
他就是谋杀了黛西 阿姆斯壮的人
</br>The man who murdered little Daisy Armstrong.

01:03:50.760 --> 01:03:52.350
我知道了
</br>I see.

01:03:52.520 --> 01:03:55.790
我承认我认识这家人 现在这男人死了
</br>I admit I know this family, and now this man is dead.

01:03:56.640 --> 01:03:57.750
这样的巧合…
</br>The coincidence...

01:03:57.920 --> 01:04:00.190
一定让人难以置信
</br>must seem unbearable.

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:03.990
巧合是允许出现的
</br>You may be permitted a coincidence.

01:04:05.840 --> 01:04:08.910
我现在要问施密特小姐几个问题
</br>I must now ask a few questions of your Fraulein Schmidt.

01:04:09.080 --> 01:04:10.450
不 没这个必要
</br>No. There is no need.

01:04:10.480 --> 01:04:11.990
我可以替她回答
</br>I can answer to her character.

01:04:12.200 --> 01:04:14.150
请您允许我亲自问她
</br>Even still, if you will allow.

01:04:15.800 --> 01:04:17.670
小姐 请你用德语回答我
</br>Fraulein. Answer please in German.

01:04:17.920 --> 01:04:19.750
但是公主殿下会听不懂
</br>But her Excellency cannot comprehend me.

01:04:20.840 --> 01:04:22.190
这才是重点
</br>That is the point.

01:04:26.480 --> 01:04:28.470
这是你的吗 H代表希尔德加德
</br>This is yours? H for Hildegarde?

01:04:31.440 --> 01:04:33.430
我不可能有这么贵重的东西
</br>It is too fine for me.

01:04:35.280 --> 01:04:37.230
公主说的昨晚的事属实吗
</br>This is the truth about last night?

01:04:38.360 --> 01:04:42.710
就像她说的一样 她让列车员来找我
</br>As she said. She sent the conductor for me,

01:04:43.200 --> 01:04:44.470
之后我就回床上去了
</br>then I returned to bed.

01:04:45.080 --> 01:04:46.560
你回去的时候有看到什么人吗
</br>Did you see anyone when you returned?

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:48.590
只有另一个列车员
</br>Only the other conductor.

01:04:49.960 --> 01:04:51.050
另一个列车员
</br>"The other conductor."

01:04:51.080 --> 01:04:52.080
你是说米歇尔吗
</br>You mean Michel?

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:55.040
不是 不是叫醒我的人 是另一个
</br>No. A different one than had awoken me.

01:04:55.840 --> 01:04:56.840
请跟我来
</br>Please come with me.

01:04:59.200 --> 01:05:00.480
你确定你没看到他吗
</br>Are you sure you did not see him?

01:05:00.520 --> 01:05:01.610
我确定 另一个列车员
</br>I'm certain. The other conductor

01:05:01.640 --> 01:05:02.850
长得不高 胡子很短
</br>was a small man with a short beard.

01:05:02.880 --> 01:05:04.090
确定吗 这里只有一个列车员
</br>Probably, there is no other conductor.

01:05:04.120 --> 01:05:05.120
我知道我看到了什么
</br>I know what I saw.

01:05:05.280 --> 01:05:06.690
我能记得是因为他的声音很高
</br>I remember because his voice was high

01:05:06.720 --> 01:05:08.010
而且穿着一样的制服
</br>and the uniform was the same exactly.

01:05:08.040 --> 01:05:09.710
不过我怀疑它少了一颗纽扣
</br>Though, I suspect, missing one button.

01:05:09.920 --> 01:05:11.470
先生 我需要立刻征用你的万能钥匙
</br>Sir, I need your passkey immediately.

01:05:11.640 --> 01:05:15.420
我们要找到一件制服和一件红色的和服
</br>We need to find a uniform and a red kimono.

01:05:15.640 --> 01:05:17.030
上千张照片
</br>Thousands of photographs,

01:05:17.120 --> 01:05:18.120
无数多的袜子…
</br>endless pairs of socks...

01:05:18.280 --> 01:05:20.110
除了红色之外所有颜色的睡衣都有…
</br>dressing gowns in every color but red...

01:05:20.280 --> 01:05:22.110
就是没有另一件制服
</br>and still no contraband conductor's uniform.

01:05:22.280 --> 01:05:24.710
你有检查所有乘客的行李吗
</br>Have we checked all the passengers' luggage?

01:05:24.880 --> 01:05:26.150
除了安德烈伯爵的行李
</br> All except for the Count

01:05:26.240 --> 01:05:27.480
先生
</br>and Countess Andrenyi, monsieur.

01:05:27.640 --> 01:05:29.590
我们不能查他们的行李
</br>It is forbidden to search their suitcases.

01:05:29.760 --> 01:05:31.550
他们是以外交签证出行的
</br>They travel under diplomatic visas.

01:05:31.720 --> 01:05:33.590
那还能是哪里呢
</br>Where else could it be?

01:05:33.760 --> 01:05:36.990
我们还有一件没查过的行李
</br>There is one last suitcase we have not checked.

01:05:38.280 --> 01:05:39.280
我的行李
</br>My own.

01:05:44.080 --> 01:05:46.310
凶手在嘲笑我
</br> The killer is mocking me.

01:05:46.480 --> 01:05:48.230
很好 他犯了第一个错误
</br>Good. His first mistake.

01:05:48.400 --> 01:05:51.430
因为夜晚之后就是白天…
</br>And as the night must follow the day...

01:05:51.600 --> 01:05:53.630
抱歉 小姐
</br>Pardon, mademoiselle.

01:05:57.400 --> 01:05:59.780
不 这不是我的
</br>No, it's not mine.

01:05:59.960 --> 01:06:01.730
我告诉过你关于列车员的事情 如果是我干的
</br>I told you of the conductor. Why would I tell you

01:06:01.760 --> 01:06:02.920
- 为什么我会告诉你这件事呢  - 你没有…
</br>- if it was me?  - You would not...

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:05.240
这让你的房间成了最适合藏它的地方
</br>which makes your compartment the ideal choice to hide it.

01:06:05.280 --> 01:06:06.550
看 就是这个纽扣
</br>Voila, the button.

01:06:06.720 --> 01:06:09.350
如果我有一件列车员的制服…
</br>And if a conductor's uniform...

01:06:09.520 --> 01:06:14.590
为什么不弄一把万能钥匙呢
</br>why not a conductor's passkey?

01:06:14.760 --> 01:06:16.030
现在我们知道凶手是怎么
</br>Now we know how the killer

01:06:16.120 --> 01:06:18.580
奇迹般地把门锁上的了
</br>magically passed through locked doors.

01:06:22.880 --> 01:06:24.630
波本 麦奎因
</br>Bourbon. MacQueen.

01:06:26.800 --> 01:06:27.890
现在你在找什么
</br>Now what are we looking for now?

01:06:27.920 --> 01:06:29.140
五百磅
</br>500 pounds.

01:06:29.320 --> 01:06:30.460
麦奎因还有一个分类帐
</br>MacQueen also had a ledger.

01:06:30.560 --> 01:06:31.910
里面有所有他和雷切特的交易
</br>All his dealings with Ratchett.

01:06:32.080 --> 01:06:33.950
恩 那它在哪里呢
</br>Where is it, hmm?

01:06:37.200 --> 01:06:38.200
波罗
</br>Poirot?

01:06:40.680 --> 01:06:42.870
布克 让所有人回房间
</br>Bouc, keep everyone inside!

01:06:44.200 --> 01:06:45.550
先生 请你等一下
</br>Monsieur! Please stop!

01:06:55.240 --> 01:06:56.240
先生
</br>Monsieur!

01:07:20.720 --> 01:07:21.910
先生
</br>Monsieur!

01:07:22.040 --> 01:07:23.390
请你站在那里别动
</br>Please stay where you are.

01:07:35.040 --> 01:07:37.270
谢谢 先生 谢谢
</br> Thank you, gentlemen. Thank you.

01:07:46.600 --> 01:07:49.470
所以 是麦奎因吗 你找到凶手了吗
</br>So, it was MacQueen? You have your man?

01:07:49.640 --> 01:07:51.150
抱歉 女士
</br>Pardonnez-moi, madame.

01:07:51.320 --> 01:07:53.230
他怎么可以
</br>How could he?

01:07:53.400 --> 01:07:54.520
我没杀他
</br>I didn't kill him!

01:07:54.560 --> 01:07:55.810
你想要烧了雷切特的账本…
</br> You tried to burn Ratchett's accounts...

01:07:55.840 --> 01:07:57.130
但是他们依旧很清晰
</br>but they are still legible in places.

01:07:57.160 --> 01:07:58.160
数字不相符…
</br>The maths do not tally...

01:07:58.320 --> 01:07:59.910
因为你是从他那里偷来的
</br>because you have been stealing from him.

01:08:00.080 --> 01:08:01.550
这全是…
</br>It is full of the...

01:08:01.760 --> 01:08:04.990
用英语怎么说的 巧克力
</br>What is the English word? The chocolat?

01:08:05.160 --> 01:08:06.190
- 夹心  - 夹心
</br>- Fudge?  - Fudge!

01:08:06.280 --> 01:08:07.420
全都是巧克力夹心
</br>It is full of the fudge!

01:08:07.640 --> 01:08:09.470
是你从他那里拿走的
</br>You stole from him!

01:08:09.640 --> 01:08:11.190
你觉得暴露
</br>You thought you would be found out.

01:08:11.360 --> 01:08:13.510
所以你杀了他
</br>That is why you killed him!

01:08:13.680 --> 01:08:14.680
没错
</br>Yeah.

01:08:15.840 --> 01:08:19.270
没错 你对了 我从他那里偷来的
</br>Yeah, you're damn right I stole from him.

01:08:19.440 --> 01:08:20.710
好几千磅
</br>Thousands.

01:08:21.760 --> 01:08:24.470
我知道他的钱来的不干净
</br>I knew his money wasn't honest.

01:08:24.640 --> 01:08:27.870
我从中抽一点又有什么关系
</br>What did it matter if I skimmed some off the top?

01:08:28.080 --> 01:08:30.990
但是让我问你一个问题
</br>But let me ask you a question.

01:08:31.160 --> 01:08:34.910
为什么我要杀掉自己的财神爷
</br>Why would I slaughter my cash cow?

01:08:35.080 --> 01:08:36.300
我没做过
</br>I didn't do it.

01:08:36.480 --> 01:08:38.200
- 我没杀他  - 他不是凶手
</br>- I didn't kill him!  - He didn't.

01:08:38.920 --> 01:08:40.060
他不是
</br>He didn't.

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:42.710
我觉得他的不在场证明和我有关
</br>I expect his alibi revolves around me,

01:08:42.800 --> 01:08:43.960
我们一直喝到凌晨
</br>drinking till the early hours.

01:08:44.120 --> 01:08:45.120
没错
</br>Well, it's true.

01:08:45.280 --> 01:08:46.990
我看他在和威士忌 然后
</br>I saw him having whiskey, and remarked

01:08:47.080 --> 01:08:48.950
评论美国酒有多难喝
</br>on the lesser quality of American liquor.

01:08:49.120 --> 01:08:50.120
他请我喝了一些
</br>He offered me a tipple

01:08:50.200 --> 01:08:51.710
想让我改变想法 之后又喝了一些
</br>to change my mind, then another.

01:08:52.320 --> 01:08:55.110
我们谈论政治 他对斯大林…
</br>We got to arguing politics. He had some...

01:08:55.960 --> 01:08:57.510
有一些意见
</br>tomfool opinions on Stalin

01:08:57.600 --> 01:08:59.480
我必须要纠正他 但是这个人是清白的
</br>I had to correct. But the man knows his spirits.

01:09:03.560 --> 01:09:05.470
我有话和你说 先生 拜托了
</br>A word, please, monsieur.

01:09:05.640 --> 01:09:07.510
你确定你和他在一起对吧
</br>You can confirm you were with him all night?

01:09:07.680 --> 01:09:09.750
没错 我们抽烟聊天一直到两点
</br>We smoked and spoke till nearly 2:00, yes.

01:09:09.920 --> 01:09:11.850
他和他的香烟 和你…
</br>Ah, such chums, him with his cigarettes, and you...

01:09:11.880 --> 01:09:14.260
是的 你是火车上唯一一个用烟斗的人
</br>Yes, you are the only man on the train who smokes a pipe.

01:09:14.440 --> 01:09:16.390
我可以看看你的烟斗和烟草吗
</br>May I see your pipe and your tobacco, please?

01:09:16.560 --> 01:09:17.560
当然可以
</br>Of course.

01:09:17.720 --> 01:09:18.720
而你 阿巴斯诺特医生
</br>And you, Dr. Arbuthnot,

01:09:18.840 --> 01:09:21.400
我想你是从印度来的对吧
</br>were traveling from India, I believe. Yes?

01:09:21.560 --> 01:09:23.390
你现在开始问我了吗 嗯
</br>You're interviewing me now? Mmm-hmm.

01:09:23.560 --> 01:09:24.730
在雷切特死之前
</br>Were you ever in Ratchett's compartment

01:09:24.760 --> 01:09:26.470
- 你去过他车厢吗  - 当然没有
</br>- before he was killed?  - Certainly not.

01:09:26.680 --> 01:09:28.720
但是这是你的烟斗清洁棒 不是吗
</br>But this is one of your pipe cleaners, n'est-ce pas?

01:09:28.800 --> 01:09:32.390
如果你是在他的车厢里找到的 问问别人吧
</br>If you found that in the dead man's cabin, look elsewhere.

01:09:32.600 --> 01:09:33.790
先生 我是个医生
</br>I am a doctor, sir.

01:09:33.920 --> 01:09:35.240
我是救人的 不是杀人的
</br>I heal people. I do not hurt them.

01:09:35.440 --> 01:09:37.070
关于这个 你为了成为医生
</br>About this, see, you must have worked

01:09:37.160 --> 01:09:38.590
一定非常认真的学习了
</br>very hard to become a doctor.

01:09:38.760 --> 01:09:42.110
你的人种里没有多少人有这样的机会
</br>Not many of your race are allowed the opportunity.

01:09:43.280 --> 01:09:45.190
米德尔赛克斯医学院每个班会招一个人
</br>Middlesex Medical College permits one per class.

01:09:45.360 --> 01:09:47.350
我有幸在一九二四年入学了
</br>I had the honor in '24.

01:09:48.760 --> 01:09:51.270
我服役时是一个狙击手
</br>I was a sniper in my tour.

01:09:51.440 --> 01:09:53.030
一个神枪手
</br>A sharpshooter.

01:09:53.200 --> 01:09:54.630
救了一些人
</br>Saved more than a few officers.

01:09:54.760 --> 01:09:55.760
他们很感激我
</br>The more grateful,

01:09:55.800 --> 01:09:57.410
肯定了我的技术…
</br>recognized a fair mind with a steady hand...

01:09:57.440 --> 01:09:59.270
并且资助了我的学业
</br>and supported my education.

01:09:59.440 --> 01:10:00.830
我不能让他们的慷慨白费
</br>I take their generosity as a debt.

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:03.150
你认识阿姆斯壮上校吗
</br>Did you know a Colonel Armstrong?

01:10:03.320 --> 01:10:06.270
我知道两三个阿姆斯壮
</br>Might have known two or three Armstrongs.

01:10:06.440 --> 01:10:08.110
六十年代的汤米 塞尔比·阿姆斯壮…
</br>Tommy in the 60th... Selby Armstrong...

01:10:08.200 --> 01:10:09.630
不 我是说约翰 阿姆斯壮上校
</br>No, I meant Colonel John Armstrong.

01:10:09.800 --> 01:10:10.990
他有一个美国妻子
</br>He had an American wife,

01:10:11.120 --> 01:10:14.270
他的孩子被绑架并且杀害了
</br>and his child was kidnapped and killed.

01:10:14.560 --> 01:10:15.620
哦
</br>Oh.

01:10:16.520 --> 01:10:17.650
不认识
</br>Never came across the fellow.

01:10:17.680 --> 01:10:19.790
你第一次见到德贝纳姆小姐是什么时候
</br>When did you first meet Miss Debenham?

01:10:19.960 --> 01:10:21.790
是从基尔库克到尼西比时
</br>We met when we shared the railway convoy car

01:10:21.880 --> 01:10:23.020
我们一起坐铁路车队车的时候
</br>from Kirkuk to Nissibin.

01:10:23.200 --> 01:10:24.260
她和我不一样
</br>She claims otherwise,

01:10:24.360 --> 01:10:26.470
她让自己非常可疑
</br>and she has made herself problematically suspicious.

01:10:26.640 --> 01:10:27.640
抱歉
</br>Excusez-moi.

01:10:27.800 --> 01:10:29.550
玛丽是一个淑女
</br>Mary is a lady.

01:10:31.320 --> 01:10:33.130
别把她牵扯进来 我可以为她的人格担保
</br>Leave her out of this. I can vouch for her character.

01:10:33.160 --> 01:10:35.150
就像你为麦奎因的时间线担保一样吗
</br>As you vouched for MacQueen's time?

01:10:38.520 --> 01:10:40.190
你一定不会想要知道原因的
</br>You won't listen to reason. Never.

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:43.670
你很幸运 好医生坚持说
</br>You are lucky. The good doctor insists

01:10:43.840 --> 01:10:45.510
你从未离开他的视线
</br>he did not let you out of his sight.

01:10:45.720 --> 01:10:47.230
看吧 我不是凶手
</br>See? There. Couldn't have done it.

01:10:47.400 --> 01:10:48.460
是的 你就是的
</br>Yes, you could.

01:10:48.680 --> 01:10:50.480
雷切特每晚都会吃一片安眠药
</br>Ratchett took a sleeping draught each evening.

01:10:50.680 --> 01:10:53.470
你很容易就可以在里面加巴比妥
</br>You could add barbital, easily access that drug.

01:10:53.680 --> 01:10:55.680
就像在医生的酒里下药一样…
</br>Do the same with one of the doctor's many drinks...

01:10:55.720 --> 01:10:57.120
很明显你有机会可以去杀他
</br>and the chance to kill him is clear.

01:10:57.240 --> 01:10:58.320
为什么我要这么做
</br>Why would I do any of that?

01:10:58.440 --> 01:10:59.650
我们已经想到了你的动机
</br>We have established your motive.

01:10:59.680 --> 01:11:01.670
或许我可以提出另外一点
</br> Perhaps I will suggest a different one.

01:11:01.840 --> 01:11:06.230
一个不一样的原因 更加私人的原因
</br>A different reason, a more personal reason.

01:11:06.400 --> 01:11:09.230
一个靠教育而非性格的律师
</br>"A lawyer by education, not by disposition."

01:11:09.400 --> 01:11:12.390
我想知道为什么你要学法律
</br>Why did you pursue the law, I wonder?

01:11:13.600 --> 01:11:17.070
是为了一个深爱的
</br>Was it to appease a much loved,

01:11:17.200 --> 01:11:19.470
但是希望子承父业的父亲…
</br>but demanding father...

01:11:20.480 --> 01:11:24.630
他在同样的领域
</br>one who himself had made a great success

01:11:24.720 --> 01:11:26.070
也很成功…
</br>in the same field...

01:11:26.240 --> 01:11:30.230
之后却失去了他的地位
</br>and then lost his position?

01:11:31.360 --> 01:11:34.470
麦昆曾经很有名 不是吗
</br>There was a renowned MacQueen, was there not?

01:11:34.680 --> 01:11:38.220
新泽西的区域律师…
</br>The district attorney for the state of New Jersey...

01:11:38.400 --> 01:11:41.390
为阿姆斯壮一案
</br>responsible for the prosecution

01:11:41.520 --> 01:11:43.670
做检察官
</br>of the Armstrong case.

01:11:46.600 --> 01:11:48.980
他们没有嫌疑人
</br>They didn't have a suspect.

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:52.910
我的父亲压力巨大
</br>My dad was pressured to go after

01:11:53.040 --> 01:11:54.870
在这个可怜的法国女人…
</br>this poor French woman...

01:11:55.080 --> 01:11:59.070
一个柔弱的女佣之后？
</br>a maid with a weak alibi, Susanne.

01:12:00.840 --> 01:12:03.070
他把整个案子都退给女佣
</br>He hung his whole case on her.

01:12:04.240 --> 01:12:07.190
她就自杀了
</br>She killed herself.

01:12:07.360 --> 01:12:10.030
她是无辜的
</br>She was innocent.

01:12:10.200 --> 01:12:13.390
当证据指向卡塞蒂的时候
</br>By the time the evidence lead to Cassetti,

01:12:13.520 --> 01:12:15.790
哦 他早已去世了
</br>oh, he was long gone.

01:12:17.080 --> 01:12:19.750
他们败坏了他的名声
</br>They tore my old man apart.

01:12:22.240 --> 01:12:24.230
我不能为他做任何事
</br>I couldn't do anything for him.

01:12:24.440 --> 01:12:25.660
所以你说
</br>And yet you claim

01:12:25.760 --> 01:12:27.750
你不知道雷切特就是卡塞蒂
</br>that you did not know Ratchett was Cassetti?

01:12:27.920 --> 01:12:29.550
不 不
</br>No, no.

01:12:29.720 --> 01:12:30.910
但是你找到他了
</br> But you found him.

01:12:31.040 --> 01:12:32.040
没有
</br>No.

01:12:32.080 --> 01:12:33.080
你找到他了
</br>You found him.

01:12:33.240 --> 01:12:34.240
- 你榨干了他…  - 没有
</br>- You bled him dry...  - No.

01:12:34.320 --> 01:12:36.670
为了给你父亲报仇
</br>in order to settle your father's debts,

01:12:36.760 --> 01:12:38.870
最后 完成计划
</br>and then finally, to settle the score.

01:12:39.080 --> 01:12:40.390
不 不 不
</br>No, no, no.

01:12:40.560 --> 01:12:42.470
不 不是…
</br>No. It wasn't...

01:12:42.640 --> 01:12:45.510
不是这样的 不是这样的…
</br>It wasn't like that. It's not the way...

01:12:48.920 --> 01:12:50.080
有人闯了进来…
</br>Someone kicked in the door...

01:12:50.120 --> 01:12:51.230
医生
</br> Doctor!

01:12:51.400 --> 01:12:52.950
蒙住了我的脸
</br>covered my face.

01:12:54.760 --> 01:12:56.630
好吧 这个要立刻拔出来
</br>All right, this needs to come out now.

01:13:02.480 --> 01:13:04.270
- 我需要我的包  - 当然
</br>- I want my bag.  - Of course.

01:13:04.480 --> 01:13:05.620
在我的车厢里
</br>It's in my compartment.

01:13:06.520 --> 01:13:07.720
这样不会留下指纹
</br>There will be no fingerprints.

01:13:07.800 --> 01:13:08.890
凶手要销毁杀人凶器
</br>The killer was disposing of the murder weapon.

01:13:09.960 --> 01:13:11.470
在这儿
</br>It's there!

01:13:20.240 --> 01:13:23.110
凶手没有刺中肺或者动脉
</br>The killer didn't hit a lung or artery.

01:13:23.280 --> 01:13:24.710
她能活下来真是幸运
</br>She's lucky to be alive.

01:13:24.920 --> 01:13:26.270
你们都很幸运
</br>You all are.

01:13:26.440 --> 01:13:27.440
是啊 天才
</br>Yeah, some genius!

01:13:27.600 --> 01:13:30.060
为什么你还不破案
</br>Why haven't you solved this case?

01:13:30.480 --> 01:13:32.430
要给他些时间
</br>You must give the man some time.

01:13:32.600 --> 01:13:33.790
是啊…
</br>Yeah, well...

01:13:33.960 --> 01:13:36.830
我等不下去了 我要死了
</br>I can't give that much more. I don't have any blood left.

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:38.000
是啊
</br>Yeah.

01:13:38.160 --> 01:13:39.380
你们询问麦奎因先生
</br>Accosting Mr. MacQueen,

01:13:39.480 --> 01:13:40.990
然而真正的凶手就在这里
</br>and the real killer is right here.

01:13:41.160 --> 01:13:42.990
你们中的一员
</br>One of you people.

01:13:45.280 --> 01:13:47.840
我不知道你是谁 我什么都没说
</br>I don't know who you are. I said nothing.

01:13:48.000 --> 01:13:49.430
拜托 别来搞我
</br>Please, leave me alone.

01:13:51.160 --> 01:13:53.150
朋友们 早上轨道就会被清理干净
</br>My friends, the tracks will be cleared by morning.

01:13:53.360 --> 01:13:54.910
拜托 回房间去
</br>Please, return to your rooms.

01:13:55.080 --> 01:13:56.080
我要在这里睡…
</br>I'm sleeping here...

01:13:56.280 --> 01:13:58.470
我们互相都可以看到的地方
</br>where everyone can see me and I can see everyone.

01:13:58.640 --> 01:14:00.330
你们都应该这么做 这样比较暖
</br>You should all do the same. Conserve heat.

01:14:00.360 --> 01:14:03.110
请大家待在视野开阔 安全的地方 直到早上
</br>Remain in the open, safely in view, until morning.

01:14:03.280 --> 01:14:04.960
凶手要再杀人的话可是不会犹豫的
</br>A killer will never hesitate to kill again.

01:14:09.400 --> 01:14:11.470
不管他有没有外交豁免权…
</br>I will convey the same message to the Andrenyis...

01:14:11.640 --> 01:14:13.190
我都会告诉他同样的话
</br>diplomatic immunity or not.

01:14:18.040 --> 01:14:20.600
如果可以的话 我想看看你的护照
</br>If I may, I will look at your passports.

01:14:26.160 --> 01:14:27.520
你知道我必须要和她聊聊
</br>You know that I must talk with her.

01:14:28.400 --> 01:14:30.170
还有 你的妻子的名字上有块油斑
</br>By the way, there is a grease spot on your wife's name.

01:14:30.200 --> 01:14:31.370
你或许想看看
</br>You might want to look at that.

01:14:31.400 --> 01:14:32.870
伊莲娜不太好
</br>Elena is not well.

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:35.530
如果你不要我这么做的话
</br>If you do not permit me, your reluctance

01:14:35.560 --> 01:14:36.730
我会告诉南斯拉夫警方你不合作…
</br>will be noted to the Yugoslav Police...

01:14:36.760 --> 01:14:38.210
而且我不确定他们会不会把你们都抓起来…
</br>and I have no doubt that they will arrest both you and...

01:14:38.240 --> 01:14:39.250
你怎么可以
</br>How dare you!

01:14:39.280 --> 01:14:40.670
亲爱的
</br>Darling!

01:14:42.080 --> 01:14:43.110
亲爱的
</br>Darling.

01:14:49.400 --> 01:14:52.230
波罗先生 你看起来真好笑
</br>You are funny-looking, monsieur Poirot.

01:14:52.400 --> 01:14:54.750
所有侦探都长的这这么好笑吗
</br>Are all detectives so funny-looking?

01:14:57.400 --> 01:15:00.670
很抱歉叫醒你 康科斯夫人
</br>I am sorry to wake you, Madame la Comtesse.

01:15:00.760 --> 01:15:02.190
嗯
</br>Hmm.

01:15:02.280 --> 01:15:04.230
我总是在夜晚醒着
</br>I am always awake at night.

01:15:04.400 --> 01:15:06.270
在白天睡觉
</br>In the day, I sleep.

01:15:06.480 --> 01:15:10.590
有些怕黑 但我忍受不了光
</br>Some fear darkness, but I cannot stand the light.

01:15:10.760 --> 01:15:12.710
你总是服用…
</br>You are always under the influence of...

01:15:13.600 --> 01:15:14.720
巴比妥
</br>Barbital.

01:15:15.280 --> 01:15:17.470
<font size="40" color="#ece0c2">巴比妥：一种镇静剂
{\rCHS}巴比妥 巴比妥
</br>Barbital, barbital.</font>

01:15:17.600 --> 01:15:19.550
我会服用很多
</br>I take oceans of it.

01:15:22.320 --> 01:15:24.390
哦 撒谎是没用的 亲爱的
</br>Oh, there's no use in a lie, love.

01:15:24.560 --> 01:15:26.590
他能看透我们
</br>He can see right through us.

01:15:28.560 --> 01:15:30.940
我不能出门不带它
</br>I cannot go outside without it.

01:15:32.080 --> 01:15:34.270
没有它我睡不着
</br>I cannot sleep without it.

01:15:36.120 --> 01:15:37.950
我用它来驱赶恐惧
</br>I take it against my fears.

01:15:43.760 --> 01:15:44.760
你的恐惧是什么
</br>What are you afraid of?

01:15:48.280 --> 01:15:49.500
一切
</br>Everything.

01:15:54.240 --> 01:15:58.910
你护照上显示你本名戈登堡
</br>Your passport has your maiden name as Goldenberg.

01:15:59.080 --> 01:16:00.430
犹太人 是吗
</br>Jewish, yes?

01:16:00.600 --> 01:16:03.160
并不是纯犹太人 我的中间名不是玛丽亚
</br>Not so Jewish. My middle name isn't Maria.

01:16:03.320 --> 01:16:04.990
那你和你丈夫一样是舞者吗
</br>And you are a dancer like your husband?

01:16:05.200 --> 01:16:07.110
不 和我丈夫不一样
</br>No, not like my husband.

01:16:07.280 --> 01:16:09.310
在芭蕾舞团
</br>Corps de ballet.

01:16:09.480 --> 01:16:10.590
他被天使触碰过
</br>He is touched by angels.

01:16:10.760 --> 01:16:12.630
我通过热情和
</br>I have been shoved by passion

01:16:12.760 --> 01:16:15.390
努力变得能胜任
</br>and hard work to become adequate.

01:16:17.960 --> 01:16:19.870
不好意思 我必须去躺着了
</br>Excuse me, I must lie down again.

01:16:20.440 --> 01:16:23.000
这是你唯一的一件睡衣吗
</br>Is this your only dressing gown?

01:16:27.840 --> 01:16:31.830
不 我还有一件 玉米色的雪纺衫
</br>No, I have another. Corn-colored chiffon.

01:16:33.160 --> 01:16:34.630
我喜欢和侦探聊天
</br>I like speaking to detectives.

01:16:34.800 --> 01:16:36.990
你永远不知道他们接下来要问什么
</br>You never know what they're going to ask you next.

01:16:37.960 --> 01:16:39.280
我对首都特别擅长
</br>I'm particularly good at capitals.

01:16:39.360 --> 01:16:41.230
我的女家教对地理十分热衷
</br>My governess was a stickler for geography.

01:16:44.160 --> 01:16:45.870
你满意了吗
</br>Are you satisfied?

01:16:46.080 --> 01:16:50.190
我总会因为发现说谎者而感到满足
</br>I am always satisfied when I uncover a liar.

01:16:50.360 --> 01:16:53.980
夫人 你的名字不是艾琳娜 而是海伦娜
</br>Madame, your name is not Elena. It is Helena.

01:16:54.160 --> 01:16:55.280
尽管你笨拙地尝试去
</br>Despite your clumsy attempts

01:16:55.360 --> 01:16:57.510
在你的行李上改动它
</br>to change it here and on your luggage.

01:16:59.240 --> 01:17:00.450
我丈夫听说
</br> My husband heard

01:17:00.480 --> 01:17:01.990
发现了一些证据…
</br>of a piece of evidence found...

01:17:02.160 --> 01:17:03.750
一块刺绣着H的手帕
</br>a handkerchief embroidered with an "H,"

01:17:03.880 --> 01:17:06.180
他不想让我因为H被牵连
</br>and didn't want my "H" Involved.

01:17:06.360 --> 01:17:09.830
所以我们做了手脚 行李还有护照
</br>So we changed it. The luggage and the passport.

01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:12.300
想要摆脱麻烦并不等同于犯罪
</br>It's no crime to want to be distant from trouble.

01:17:12.520 --> 01:17:14.190
是 但问题就是
</br>Yet, here is trouble.

01:17:14.400 --> 01:17:15.620
一个令人好奇的细节是
</br>A curious detail

01:17:15.720 --> 01:17:18.180
在阿姆斯壮惨案中…
</br>about the Armstrong tragedy at the heart of this case...

01:17:18.400 --> 01:17:21.910
有多少人受到了伤害
</br>is how many people were wounded by it.

01:17:22.080 --> 01:17:23.870
妹妹
</br>The younger sister.

01:17:24.040 --> 01:17:25.910
作为演员的母亲…
</br>The actress mother...

01:17:26.120 --> 01:17:29.350
艺名为 雅顿·琳达
</br>stage name, Linda Arden.

01:17:29.360 --> 01:17:33.270
{\i1\bord5\shad0\c&H222627&\3c&7C8180&\3a&H00&}诚挚地感谢您睿智的来信　雅顿·琳达
{\rCHS}我猜她的祖先也是犹太人…
</br>I suppose she, too, was of Jewish ancestry...

01:17:33.400 --> 01:17:36.910
那么谁最有可能有一个艺名
</br>as who is most likely to take a stage name?

01:17:37.080 --> 01:17:40.030
就无法推测了…
</br>Is it too far to suggest...

01:17:40.200 --> 01:17:43.190
她的原名是戈登堡
</br>her original name was Goldenberg?

01:17:44.400 --> 01:17:47.350
尤其是我们发现了一位年轻的女士
</br>Especially when we find a young woman,

01:17:47.440 --> 01:17:48.910
年龄相仿…
</br>the same age...

01:17:49.080 --> 01:17:51.870
作为她幸存的女儿…
</br>as her surviving daughter...

01:17:52.040 --> 01:17:54.270
生活在恐惧之中
</br>living in a world of fear?

01:17:54.960 --> 01:17:58.070
他的妹妹 索尼亚 阿姆斯特朗
</br>The sister of Sonia Armstrong.

01:17:59.920 --> 01:18:01.110
出去
</br>Get out!

01:18:05.720 --> 01:18:09.230
我听到声音就跑过来了 刚刚好 是吗
</br>I hear noises and I run. Just in time, yes?

01:18:09.400 --> 01:18:12.310
你现在一定认为伯爵和伯爵夫人是凶手
</br>You must now believe the count and countess are the killers.

01:18:12.440 --> 01:18:13.440
伯爵是自我防卫
</br>The count is protective.

01:18:13.480 --> 01:18:15.250
伯爵夫人连房间里的一只蜘蛛都杀不死
</br>The countess would no sooner kill a bedroom spider.

01:18:15.280 --> 01:18:17.470
你不用再装了
</br>And you may desist with this charade.

01:18:19.280 --> 01:18:22.550
你既不是奥地利人也不是德国人 更不是什么教授
</br>You are neither an Austrian, nor a German, nor a professor.

01:18:23.280 --> 01:18:24.990
而是一位出色的模仿者
</br>But a good imitation.

01:18:25.120 --> 01:18:27.270
是模仿了某个你认识的人吗
</br>Was it based on someone you know?

01:18:32.640 --> 01:18:36.550
我出生地的一位德国屠夫
</br>A local butcher where I grew up was a Kraut.

01:18:36.720 --> 01:18:39.550
一个好人 纯正的口音
</br>Good man, great accent.

01:18:43.200 --> 01:18:44.470
为什么这么说
</br>What was it?

01:18:44.640 --> 01:18:46.350
<font size="40" color="#ece0c2">都灵：意大利城市
{\rCHS}你说了 都灵…
</br>You said "Tur-in..."</font>

01:18:46.520 --> 01:18:48.350
重音的音节不对
</br>the emphasis on the wrong syllable

01:18:48.480 --> 01:18:50.150
一个正统的日耳曼人会说
</br>for a proud and proper Teuton.

01:18:50.720 --> 01:18:52.310
都灵
</br>"Tu-reen."

01:18:55.560 --> 01:18:59.910
你十分敏锐 我承认
</br>You are one sharp knife, I give you that.

01:19:04.480 --> 01:19:08.150
格哈德哈德曼教授…
</br>Herr Professor Gerhard Hardman...

01:19:08.320 --> 01:19:10.230
是我的假名
</br>is my cover.

01:19:10.400 --> 01:19:12.830
抱歉上演了一出种族歧视的戏码
</br>I'm sorry about the colored folks cracks.

01:19:13.000 --> 01:19:15.990
我也算半个犹太人
</br>Hell, I'm half a Heeb myself.

01:19:16.160 --> 01:19:19.150
塞勒斯 贝思曼 哈德曼
</br>Cyrus Bethman Hardman.

01:19:21.000 --> 01:19:22.350
你是平克顿的侦探
</br>You are a Pinkerton detective?

01:19:22.520 --> 01:19:24.430
三十年
</br>30 years.

01:19:24.600 --> 01:19:26.510
当时我在斯坦布尔 刚做完一个任务
</br>I was in Stamboul, coming back from a job,

01:19:26.600 --> 01:19:27.630
接到了公司的电报
</br>when the office cabled.

01:19:27.720 --> 01:19:30.390
雷切特需要一个人保护他
</br>Ratchett asked for a man to tail him,

01:19:30.520 --> 01:19:31.660
出三倍的价格
</br>offering triple time.

01:19:31.840 --> 01:19:33.830
而我就是那个人
</br>Lucky me being nearby.

01:19:39.400 --> 01:19:41.430
他让我注意
</br>He told me to look out

01:19:41.520 --> 01:19:44.230
一个矮的 声音很尖的黑人
</br>for a small, dark man with a high voice.

01:19:44.920 --> 01:19:46.390
我整晚都…
</br>I watched that hall...

01:19:46.560 --> 01:19:49.430
从门缝盯着走廊
</br>all night through a crack in my door.

01:19:49.600 --> 01:19:50.710
任何刺客…
</br>Any thug...

01:19:50.880 --> 01:19:53.230
都会先经过我
</br>had to go by me first.

01:19:54.640 --> 01:19:55.910
我发誓这是真的
</br>I'll take my oath on it.

01:19:56.080 --> 01:19:58.270
那你是否愿意发誓…
</br>And would you also take your oath...

01:19:58.480 --> 01:20:01.040
你做了三十年侦探…
</br>on your thirty years as a Pinkerton Detective...

01:20:01.200 --> 01:20:02.750
还是继续向我撒谎…
</br>or would you lie to me again...

01:20:02.920 --> 01:20:06.430
然后否认你是一个警察
</br>and deny that you were, in fact, a policeman first?

01:20:06.600 --> 01:20:10.030
你的枪 枪托上的格纹 蓝色的漆面…
</br>Your gun, the checkered grip, the blue finish...

01:20:10.240 --> 01:20:13.270
是特警用的
</br>produced for the Police Positive edition.

01:20:13.440 --> 01:20:16.070
一九二七年的
</br>1927 issue.

01:20:16.240 --> 01:20:17.760
看来你为我准备了
</br>It appears there are no end to the lies

01:20:17.880 --> 01:20:19.470
一箩筐的谎言
</br>manufactured just for me.

01:20:21.320 --> 01:20:24.070
把枪留下你可以走了 教授
</br>You can leave your gun as you go, Professor.

01:20:44.240 --> 01:20:46.910
从他车厢的位置…
</br>From the position of his cabin...

01:20:48.800 --> 01:20:51.990
是不可能错过的
</br>it would have been impossible to miss.

01:20:54.160 --> 01:20:57.830
除非雷切特的门是开着的…
</br>Unless Ratchett's door was open...

01:20:58.040 --> 01:21:01.950
正如皮拉尔 埃斯特拉瓦多斯说她开了
</br>as Pilar Estravados claims she opened it.

01:21:02.120 --> 01:21:05.430
这样的话 就有人可能…
</br>In which case, someone could have been...

01:21:05.600 --> 01:21:07.980
逃脱他的视线
</br>masked from his view.

01:21:14.000 --> 01:21:15.270
我亲爱的凯瑟琳
</br>My darling Katherine.

01:21:17.040 --> 01:21:19.630
这起惨案…
</br>This is an abominable crime...

01:21:19.800 --> 01:21:22.950
我陷入了困境 凯瑟琳
</br>and I am stuck, ma Katherine.

01:21:26.000 --> 01:21:28.630
我无法找到破绽
</br>I cannot find the crack in the wall.

01:21:29.800 --> 01:21:32.830
为什么他们中有人迷惑了我
</br>Why does one of them elude me?

01:21:37.680 --> 01:21:39.550
我一直都…
</br>I have always been...

01:21:40.520 --> 01:21:42.150
很笃定
</br>so sure.

01:21:43.480 --> 01:21:45.230
太笃定
</br>Too sure.

01:21:47.480 --> 01:21:49.030
但现在 我就像一个孩子一样
</br>But now, I am very humble.

01:21:49.160 --> 01:21:51.620
谦卑地说…
</br>And I say, like a little child...

01:21:54.200 --> 01:21:56.150
我不知道
</br>I do not know.

01:21:59.240 --> 01:22:01.830
我恨害怕 凯瑟琳
</br>I am afraid, ma Katherine.

01:22:17.480 --> 01:22:19.010
女士们先生们 我很抱歉
</br>My apologies, ladies and gentlemen.

01:22:19.040 --> 01:22:20.260
当在装引擎的时候
</br>It is not safe on board

01:22:20.360 --> 01:22:22.080
在列车上不安全
</br>whilst the engine is put back on the tracks.

01:22:22.120 --> 01:22:23.680
我们去隧道那边等一下 谢谢
</br>We are to wait in the tunnel. Thank you.

01:22:23.720 --> 01:22:25.090
他们要把狗带到哪里去
</br>Where are they taking the dogs?

01:22:25.120 --> 01:22:26.450
他们会很开心的
</br>They'll be happy.

01:22:26.480 --> 01:22:27.540
不会的
</br>That's not right.

01:22:27.640 --> 01:22:29.120
只是伸了伸腿 很好
</br>Just to stretch their legs, it's good.

01:22:29.280 --> 01:22:31.070
不 不对
</br>No, that's not right.

01:22:32.400 --> 01:22:33.540
冷死了
</br>It's freezing!

01:22:34.280 --> 01:22:36.190
我们是困住了吗
</br>Are we stuck?

01:22:36.360 --> 01:22:38.430
你找我吗
</br>You asked for me?

01:22:38.640 --> 01:22:39.750
又要审讯吗
</br>Another interrogation?

01:22:39.920 --> 01:22:42.350
哦不 我非常开心有你的陪伴
</br>Oh, no. I enjoy your company.

01:22:42.560 --> 01:22:43.830
谢谢你 布克
</br>Merci, Bouc.

01:22:44.000 --> 01:22:45.110
啊 请坐
</br>Uh, please.

01:22:46.760 --> 01:22:49.350
我这里列了十个 我无法解答的问题…
</br>I have a list of ten questions I am no nearer to answering...

01:22:49.520 --> 01:22:51.430
这列车就要开了
</br>and the train is about to leave.

01:22:51.600 --> 01:22:53.790
你很聪明…
</br>You have a clear mind...

01:22:53.960 --> 01:22:57.710
我认为你可能可以看出点什么 请
</br>and I thought that you might produce an insight. Please.

01:22:59.440 --> 01:23:00.710
呃
</br>Hmm.

01:23:02.280 --> 01:23:05.350
手绢 烟斗通条
</br>"The handkerchief. The pipe cleaner.

01:23:05.520 --> 01:23:09.190
红色和服 制服
</br>"The scarlet kimono. The uniform.

01:23:09.360 --> 01:23:11.550
手表上的时间
</br>"The time on the watch.

01:23:11.720 --> 01:23:15.550
谋杀发生在当时 之前还是之后
</br>"Was he murdered then? Earlier or later?

01:23:15.760 --> 01:23:18.140
被一个人杀害还是多个人
</br>"By one person or more?

01:23:18.320 --> 01:23:20.030
哪些人
</br>"Which of them?"

01:23:23.080 --> 01:23:24.790
不好意思 我无法帮助你
</br>Sorry, I can't help you.

01:23:24.960 --> 01:23:27.390
呃…谢谢你
</br>Uh... Merci.

01:23:29.160 --> 01:23:30.530
大概还有第十一个疑问
</br>Perhaps there is an eleventh question

01:23:30.560 --> 01:23:31.870
你现在不知道…
</br>you don't know to ask yet...

01:23:32.040 --> 01:23:34.230
它会为你解答其他所有问题
</br>that will give you the answer to the rest.

01:23:34.440 --> 01:23:35.710
也许吧
</br>Perhaps.

01:23:36.920 --> 01:23:40.830
我可以轻易地说安德烈伯爵夫人
</br>I could point an easy finger at the, uh, Countess Andrenyi.

01:23:41.000 --> 01:23:43.430
我发现她是索尼亚 阿姆斯特朗的妹妹
</br>I discovered she was Sonia Armstrong's sister.

01:23:43.600 --> 01:23:44.950
- 你确定吗  - 确定
</br>- Are you certain?  - Yes.

01:23:45.160 --> 01:23:46.790
我估计她大概是清白的
</br>I suspect she may perhaps be innocent.

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:48.350
只是可能
</br>Perhaps.

01:23:48.520 --> 01:23:49.910
但是列车上的很多人都
</br>But so many people have lied to me

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:51.290
有意无意地对我撒了谎
</br>on this train and do not seem to mind.

01:23:51.320 --> 01:23:52.670
而你做得毫不费力
</br>You yourself did so effortlessly.

01:23:52.760 --> 01:23:53.760
我
</br>Me?

01:23:53.960 --> 01:23:55.630
你曾告诉我你从未去过美国
</br>You told me you had never been to America.

01:23:55.840 --> 01:23:57.030
你同样隐藏了
</br>You also concealed the fact

01:23:57.120 --> 01:23:58.290
当阿姆斯特朗惨案发生时…
</br>that at the time of the tragedy...

01:23:58.320 --> 01:24:00.350
你就在他家担任…
</br>you were living in the Armstrong household...

01:24:00.520 --> 01:24:01.910
她们女儿家教的事实
</br>as governess to their daughter.

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:03.060
你也知道这一切
</br>And you know this.

01:24:03.240 --> 01:24:05.110
我也要生存
</br>I have my living to get.

01:24:05.280 --> 01:24:07.200
一个牵连进谋杀案的女人…
</br>A girl detained in connection to a murder case...

01:24:07.320 --> 01:24:08.910
不会有其他人愿意雇佣我的
</br>no decent class family would engage me.

01:24:09.080 --> 01:24:11.790
德贝纳姆小姐 是你一手策划了对雷切特的谋杀
</br>Miss Debenham, you planned Ratchett's murder.

01:24:11.960 --> 01:24:14.030
然后你让伯爵夫人作为证人
</br>And then you sent for the countess to witness it.

01:24:14.200 --> 01:24:15.670
如果她看见他死了
</br>If she saw him dead,

01:24:15.760 --> 01:24:17.270
那个你认识的海琳娜就可能回来
</br>the Helena you knew might return.

01:24:17.440 --> 01:24:19.600
你想等你的室友睡着 但她没有
</br>You waited for your roommate to sleep, but she did not.

01:24:19.720 --> 01:24:20.720
你给她下了药
</br>You drugged her.

01:24:20.800 --> 01:24:22.170
但巴比妥只让她头疼
</br>But the barbital only gave her a headache.

01:24:22.200 --> 01:24:23.530
当列车停下的时候她要了阿司匹林
</br>She begged for an aspirin when the train stopped,

01:24:23.560 --> 01:24:25.120
列车员去了站台…
</br>when the conductor was on the station...

01:24:25.200 --> 01:24:26.330
周围没了人…
</br>when the coast was clear at last...

01:24:26.360 --> 01:24:27.450
你终于有机会在没人能
</br>when you were allowed to enter

01:24:27.480 --> 01:24:28.680
发现的时候进入雷切特的房间
</br>Ratchett's compartment, unseen.

01:24:28.840 --> 01:24:30.990
你爱黛西 阿姆斯特朗 是你杀了卡塞蒂
</br>You loved Daisy Armstrong. You killed Cassetti.

01:24:35.080 --> 01:24:36.670
卡塞蒂就是一头畜生
</br>Cassetti was a pig.

01:24:36.880 --> 01:24:38.590
他该死
</br>He deserved to die.

01:24:47.280 --> 01:24:49.030
她没有杀他
</br>She didn't kill him.

01:24:51.240 --> 01:24:52.870
我杀的
</br>I did.

01:24:57.560 --> 01:24:58.910
玛丽 快走
</br>Mary, go.

01:24:59.960 --> 01:25:01.590
我不会让你因为…
</br>I can't let you take the blame...

01:25:01.760 --> 01:25:03.190
我一人的罪行而被指控
</br>for what I did alone.

01:25:08.720 --> 01:25:10.390
玛丽 求你了 走吧
</br>Mary, please, go.

01:25:13.960 --> 01:25:15.470
约翰 阿姆斯特朗是我最好的朋友
</br>John Armstrong was my best friend,

01:25:15.560 --> 01:25:17.230
我的指挥官
</br>my commander.

01:25:19.200 --> 01:25:20.950
他十分信任我
</br>He believed in me.

01:25:21.720 --> 01:25:25.110
他送我去了医学院 给了我未来
</br>He sent me to medical school, gave me a future.

01:25:26.320 --> 01:25:28.620
卡塞蒂把他给毁了
</br>Cassetti destroyed him.

01:25:30.840 --> 01:25:32.990
悲哀中 我认识了玛丽
</br>In grief, I found Mary.

01:25:34.680 --> 01:25:36.630
然后发现了雷切特
</br>Then I found Ratchett.

01:25:38.440 --> 01:25:40.510
我们本来计划向警察揭发他
</br>Our plan was to reveal him to the police,

01:25:40.600 --> 01:25:42.710
正如你之前所听到的
</br>that's what you heard.

01:25:43.720 --> 01:25:46.310
但每当我看见他的脸…
</br>But when I saw his face...

01:25:48.240 --> 01:25:50.470
我知道他不配受到审判
</br>I knew he didn't deserve a trial.

01:25:50.920 --> 01:25:54.190
所以是你对麦奎因下了药
</br>So, you drugged MacQueen.

01:25:54.360 --> 01:25:56.430
你拨动了表上的时间…
</br>You changed the time on the watch...

01:25:56.600 --> 01:25:59.550
以至于你能捏造死亡时间
</br>so that you could lie about the time of death.

01:25:59.720 --> 01:26:02.150
我不能让你指控玛丽
</br>I couldn't let Mary be accused.

01:26:02.320 --> 01:26:03.590
或者麦昆
</br>Or MacQueen.

01:26:05.120 --> 01:26:08.470
我犯的罪我一人承担
</br>My sins are mine to pay for, alone.

01:26:09.160 --> 01:26:10.790
我是一名军人
</br>I'm a soldier.

01:26:10.960 --> 01:26:12.510
军人为了保护而杀人
</br>A soldier kills to protect.

01:26:13.560 --> 01:26:14.910
但是现在 波洛先生
</br>And now, Mr. Poirot,

01:26:15.000 --> 01:26:16.470
我必须保护自己
</br>I must protect myself from you.

01:26:26.880 --> 01:26:29.710
你为什么还不死
</br>Why aren't you dead yet?

01:26:33.400 --> 01:26:36.510
波洛
</br>Poirot?

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:52.790
先生们 停一下
</br>Gentlemen, stop!

01:26:53.720 --> 01:26:55.230
先生 我们要让所有乘客
</br>Sir, we need to get all the passengers

01:26:55.320 --> 01:26:56.790
都回到车上
</br>back on the train.

01:26:58.040 --> 01:27:00.190
在我让你们回来之前…
</br>You will retire...

01:27:00.400 --> 01:27:02.430
你们都不能…
</br>away from the train...

01:27:04.000 --> 01:27:06.830
继续回到火车上
</br>until I tell you to return.

01:27:25.120 --> 01:27:26.910
你们说的谎言…
</br>You tell your lies...

01:27:27.720 --> 01:27:29.910
以为没有人能看穿
</br>and you think no one will know.

01:27:30.680 --> 01:27:33.140
但有两个人会知道
</br>But there are two people who will know.

01:27:33.640 --> 01:27:35.430
是的 两个人
</br>Yes, two people.

01:27:36.320 --> 01:27:37.790
上帝…
</br>Your God...

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:41.350
和赫尔克里 波洛
</br>and Hercule Poirot.

01:27:45.160 --> 01:27:48.350
是时候解决这个案子了
</br>It is time to solve this case.

01:28:09.400 --> 01:28:13.310
阿布思诺医生问我为什么还不死
</br>Dr. Arbuthnot asked me why I was not yet dead.

01:28:14.440 --> 01:28:16.790
他当然知道答案
</br>He knew, of course, the answer.

01:28:17.320 --> 01:28:20.030
神枪手这么近距离却没有杀人
</br>A sharpshooter who does not kill at close range?

01:28:21.800 --> 01:28:24.990
你不是失手开枪 你在帮我
</br>Your shot was not a mistake. It was a surgery.

01:28:25.640 --> 01:28:28.430
你下不了手 因为你不是杀手
</br>You could not kill me because you are no killer.

01:28:29.840 --> 01:28:32.030
你们全都不是杀手
</br>None of you are killers.

01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:35.510
但是 一定有人是
</br>And yet, someone must be.

01:28:38.400 --> 01:28:40.830
这件案子有两种可能的答案
</br>There are two possible solutions to this crime.

01:28:42.440 --> 01:28:43.930
一种很难 因为它符合了大部分的
</br>One difficult, because it fits with most

01:28:43.960 --> 01:28:45.100
却不是全部的事实…
</br>but not all of the facts...

01:28:45.280 --> 01:28:47.030
另一种…
</br>and one more...

01:28:47.200 --> 01:28:48.870
很复杂
</br>complex.

01:28:49.840 --> 01:28:51.830
第一种答案
</br>The first solution.

01:28:52.000 --> 01:28:53.710
雷切特有敌人
</br>Ratchett had enemies.

01:28:53.880 --> 01:28:56.830
罪恶的黑手党在温科夫齐偷偷潜上火车…
</br>A rogue Mafioso steals onto the train at Vinkovci...

01:28:56.920 --> 01:28:59.220
趁着麦奎因和阿巴斯诺特下车透气的时候
</br>as MacQueen and Arbuthnot take the air.

01:28:59.400 --> 01:29:00.750
带着一套制服
</br>Equipped with a uniform

01:29:00.840 --> 01:29:02.430
还有万能钥匙 他刺死了雷切特
</br>and a passkey, he stabs Ratchett.

01:29:02.600 --> 01:29:04.550
通过赫伯德女士的隔间离开
</br>He leaves through Mrs. Hubbard's compartment,

01:29:04.640 --> 01:29:05.780
然后逃跑
</br>and makes his escape.

01:29:06.080 --> 01:29:07.080
不
</br>No.

01:29:07.760 --> 01:29:10.630
不 不 不 这不成立
</br>No, no, no. It doesn't work.

01:29:11.320 --> 01:29:13.230
那为什么把制服藏起来
</br>Why hide the uniform, hmm?

01:29:13.720 --> 01:29:15.310
谁给雷切特下了药
</br>Who drugs Ratchett?

01:29:15.480 --> 01:29:17.510
谁刺伤了赫伯德女士
</br>Or stabs Mrs. Hubbard?

01:29:17.960 --> 01:29:19.630
搞错了 老天
</br>Damn it, man!

01:29:20.800 --> 01:29:23.430
所以我才问 这对谁有好处
</br>So I ask, who stands to benefit?

01:29:23.960 --> 01:29:27.710
这是对谋杀者的谋杀
</br>This crime is the murdering of a murderer.

